1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,074
Delicious Vegan Sausages, Cheese
and Burgers - Vegusto.co.uk

2
00:00:48,966 --> 00:00:50,709
We got cenizo...

3
00:00:50,926 --> 00:00:53,049
...that's purple sage...

4
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:56,588
...agave, nopal....

5
00:00:58,934 --> 00:01:00,428
What's that stuff?

6
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:03,892
That's whatchamacallit.

7
00:01:06,817 --> 00:01:08,560
That's horse crippler.

8
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:13,063
This place is a gold mine.

9
00:01:13,657 --> 00:01:15,068
Lead mine.

10
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:16,565
What?

11
00:01:16,660 --> 00:01:18,569
I said it's a lead mine.

12
00:01:18,745 --> 00:01:20,868
- Right.
- Why am I talking to you?

13
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:22,830
You got that thing on your head.

14
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:25,158
You find lots of cactus and shit?

15
00:01:25,252 --> 00:01:27,458
Not just cactus. There's acacias...

16
00:01:27,629 --> 00:01:31,248
- ...the yuccas....
- Looks like a lot of cactus to me.

17
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:36,087
Man knows 150 varieties of beer,
can't tell a poinsettia from a prickly pear.

18
00:01:37,306 --> 00:01:38,301
Cliff!

19
00:01:38,474 --> 00:01:41,807
You live in a place,
you should learn about it.

20
00:01:42,144 --> 00:01:44,635
- Explore.
- You've got to look at this.

21
00:01:46,482 --> 00:01:47,727
Don't tell me.

22
00:01:47,816 --> 00:01:49,773
Spanish treasure, right?

23
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:50,939
Pieces of eight...

24
00:01:51,028 --> 00:01:53,270
...from the Coronado Expedition.

25
00:01:59,912 --> 00:02:01,110
Jesus!

26
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:19,838
Was Coronado in the Masons?

27
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:31,159
The forensics fella's coming down
from San Marcos.

28
00:03:32,087 --> 00:03:35,752
There's no way to know how old
the body is without lab work.

29
00:03:35,966 --> 00:03:37,377
That ring?

30
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:40,469
Mason's been around a long while.

31
00:03:42,097 --> 00:03:43,722
He a treasure hunter?

32
00:03:44,516 --> 00:03:46,058
Old bullets.

33
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:48,178
Makes art out of them.

34
00:03:51,398 --> 00:03:54,434
Sheriff says
we shouldn't touch anything.

35
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:56,727
He can't hear with that rig on.

36
00:03:56,904 --> 00:03:58,481
Mikey!

37
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:00,864
Hey, what have we got here?

38
00:04:06,455 --> 00:04:09,325
We're supposed to leave everything
where we found it.

39
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,243
They're real particular about that.

40
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:15,330
The scene of the crime.

41
00:04:17,925 --> 00:04:20,676
No telling yet if there's been a crime...

42
00:04:23,222 --> 00:04:27,515
...but this country's seen a good number
of disagreements over the years.

43
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:40,393
He went to school on the post
when we were in Korea.

44
00:04:40,489 --> 00:04:43,406
It's all kids in the same boat, army brats--

45
00:04:44,243 --> 00:04:46,319
His record shows
he's a good student.

46
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:51,239
I'm more worried about the social thing.
Are there, like, gangs or guns--

47
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:54,785
We haven't had any
serious violence, if that's what you mean.

48
00:04:54,878 --> 00:04:58,247
But we've got a pretty lively mix.
Mexican kids...

49
00:04:58,340 --> 00:04:59,882
...anglo kids, black kids.

50
00:04:59,967 --> 00:05:02,802
- And the blacks are what?
- The smallest group.

51
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:04,167
Except for a couple...

52
00:05:04,263 --> 00:05:05,591
...of Kickapoo kids.

53
00:05:05,681 --> 00:05:08,598
Look, you're obviously a concerned parent.

54
00:05:09,101 --> 00:05:12,185
Chet has no history of getting into trouble.

55
00:05:12,396 --> 00:05:13,427
Pilar....

56
00:05:14,106 --> 00:05:15,220
Is Amado okay?

57
00:05:15,899 --> 00:05:17,228
He's not here?

58
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:18,231
Is he sick?

59
00:05:19,611 --> 00:05:21,770
He's going to wish he was dead.

60
00:05:43,302 --> 00:05:45,460
Somebody hand me a CD player.

61
00:05:47,723 --> 00:05:51,471
They've come a long way
since those old eight-tracks, ain't they?

62
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,805
Something wrong?

63
00:05:52,895 --> 00:05:56,145
Stolen property. I'm hauling
the bunch of you to jail.

64
00:05:56,482 --> 00:05:59,436
If anything else is wrong,
tell me on the way to the station.

65
00:06:02,654 --> 00:06:05,739
Cleaning his toenails
with a pocketknife.

66
00:06:05,824 --> 00:06:08,991
<i>He was the most hygienic</i>
<i>of all the McHenry's.</i>

67
00:06:10,287 --> 00:06:13,490
<i>"Fishbait," Buddy says,</i>
<i>in that quiet way of his...</i>

68
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:17,622
..."what do you know about the tires
that went missing from Merkel's?"

69
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:19,586
Fishbait thinks for a minute...

70
00:06:19,671 --> 00:06:22,672
...then lifts up a loose board
from the porch floor...

71
00:06:22,966 --> 00:06:24,959
...and calls down into it.

72
00:06:25,511 --> 00:06:28,595
"Come on out, Hooter, they caught us!"

73
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:32,722
Buddy Deeds, he had a way.

74
00:06:32,810 --> 00:06:35,976
He'd known who it was
from the tire tracks in the dirt...

75
00:06:36,063 --> 00:06:39,183
...leading from the back of the garage
to where they loaded up.

76
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:40,685
"Old Fishbait," he said...

77
00:06:40,776 --> 00:06:44,524
..."never lifted a thing,
if there was a way he could roll it."

78
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:48,400
Never be another like him.

79
00:06:48,492 --> 00:06:50,947
You know that boy of his can't cut it.

80
00:06:51,203 --> 00:06:53,279
He's all hat and no cattle.

81
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:55,202
Hey, fellas.

82
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,459
We was telling a few on your old man.

83
00:07:01,547 --> 00:07:03,872
He was a unique individual.

84
00:07:04,049 --> 00:07:05,543
He was that.

85
00:07:06,301 --> 00:07:07,677
Big day coming up.

86
00:07:07,803 --> 00:07:11,053
I wish we'd have thought of it
while he was still living.

87
00:07:11,306 --> 00:07:12,765
Went so unexpected.

88
00:07:13,058 --> 00:07:14,967
Better late than never.

89
00:07:15,227 --> 00:07:18,726
Korean War hero,
sheriff for nearly 30 years....

90
00:07:19,231 --> 00:07:21,804
The Buddy Deeds Memorial Courthouse.

91
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:24,226
I heard there was a bit of a fuss.

92
00:07:25,487 --> 00:07:27,480
Well, the usual troublemakers.

93
00:07:27,739 --> 00:07:31,239
Danny Padilla from the <i>Sentinel</i>.
That crowd.

94
00:07:31,410 --> 00:07:35,028
We call everything else in the country
after Martin Luther King.

95
00:07:35,164 --> 00:07:38,449
We can't have one measly courthouse?

96
00:07:38,542 --> 00:07:40,120
King wasn't Mexican, Fenton.

97
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:43,164
Bad enough
that all the street names are in Spanish.

98
00:07:43,255 --> 00:07:45,046
They were here first.

99
00:07:45,174 --> 00:07:49,586
Then let's call it after Big Chief
Shit-In-The-Bucket. That Tonkawa had...

100
00:07:49,678 --> 00:07:51,053
<i>...the Mexes beat by centuries.</i>

101
00:07:51,138 --> 00:07:54,055
Nineteen out of 20 people here
are Mexican.

102
00:07:55,017 --> 00:07:58,551
There was a faction pulling
for that boy killed in the Gulf War--

103
00:07:58,854 --> 00:08:00,681
Yeah. Santiago.

104
00:08:00,856 --> 00:08:03,145
Mexicans that know remember what...

105
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:04,858
<i>...Buddy was for their people.</i>

106
00:08:04,943 --> 00:08:07,150
<i>Hell, it was Mercedes over there</i>
<i>who swung...</i>

107
00:08:07,237 --> 00:08:08,815
...the deciding vote for him.

108
00:08:09,865 --> 00:08:11,656
<i>She made it an even 3-3.</i>

109
00:08:11,867 --> 00:08:14,358
As mayor, I get to cast the tiebreaker.

110
00:08:14,786 --> 00:08:19,283
The old-timers won't have a problem.
They know how Buddy come to be sheriff.

111
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,368
Tell that story, Hollis.

112
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:23,618
Everybody heard it a million times.

113
00:08:23,879 --> 00:08:25,373
I'd like to hear it.

114
00:08:26,298 --> 00:08:27,496
Your version of it.

115
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:29,419
Yeah, come on, Hollis.

116
00:08:32,805 --> 00:08:34,085
Well, the two of us...

117
00:08:34,473 --> 00:08:36,679
<i>...were the only deputies back then.</i>

118
00:08:37,309 --> 00:08:39,551
Me and Buddy, in what, '58?

119
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:41,645
'57, I think.

120
00:08:41,814 --> 00:08:45,396
The sheriff at the time
was big Charlie Wade.

121
00:08:46,568 --> 00:08:47,564
Charlie...

122
00:08:47,653 --> 00:08:51,900
...was one of your old-fashioned
bribe-or-bullets kind of sheriffs.

123
00:08:52,324 --> 00:08:56,073
He took a healthy bite out of whatever
moved through this country.

124
00:08:56,245 --> 00:08:58,237
It was in here one night...

125
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:01,036
<i>...back when Jimmy Herrera run the place.</i>

126
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:04,168
<i>Started over a basket of tortillas.</i>

127
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:15,467
This beaner fare doesn't agree with me
but the price sure is right.

128
00:09:17,599 --> 00:09:21,431
Jimmy got a kitchen full of wetbacks,
most of them relatives.

129
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:23,929
Those people breed like chickens.

130
00:09:26,775 --> 00:09:27,806
So?

131
00:09:28,610 --> 00:09:32,690
I roust some <i>muchacho</i> on the street
with no papers, all he's got to say is:

132
00:09:32,781 --> 00:09:34,774
<i>I work for Jimmy Herrera.</i>

133
00:09:36,493 --> 00:09:37,822
Sort of a...

134
00:09:37,995 --> 00:09:42,491
...I-scratch-his-back-he-washes-mine
arrangement, if you know what I mean.

135
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:48,753
This'll be one of your pickups.
First of the month, like the rent.

136
00:09:49,214 --> 00:09:50,708
Get the car, Hollis.

137
00:09:58,056 --> 00:09:59,716
I'm not doing it.

138
00:10:05,397 --> 00:10:06,808
Come again?

139
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:09,108
It's your deal.

140
00:10:10,235 --> 00:10:12,940
There's going to be some left over for you.

141
00:10:13,030 --> 00:10:14,524
I take care of my boys.

142
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:16,941
That's not the point, Charlie.

143
00:10:17,409 --> 00:10:19,568
You feeling bad about Jimmy?

144
00:10:19,912 --> 00:10:24,823
Ask him how big a <i>mordida</i> they took
when he run a place on the other side.

145
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:27,326
Those old boys from Ciudad León--

146
00:10:27,586 --> 00:10:29,164
I'm not picking it up.

147
00:10:31,173 --> 00:10:34,756
You do whatever I say you do
or else you put it on the trail, son.

148
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:43,683
How about this, Charlie?

149
00:10:45,437 --> 00:10:48,889
How about you lay that shield
on this table and vanish...

150
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:52,106
...before you end up dead...

151
00:10:52,361 --> 00:10:53,606
...or in jail?

152
00:10:57,991 --> 00:11:00,031
You're not making sense, Buddy.

153
00:11:00,118 --> 00:11:03,570
Stick around and I'm bringing up charges
on the county road project.

154
00:11:03,664 --> 00:11:06,451
Two-thirds of that money went straight
into your pocket.

155
00:11:09,962 --> 00:11:12,797
You're being mighty careless
with your mouth, son.

156
00:11:19,179 --> 00:11:22,180
You ever shoot a man
who's looking you in the eye?

157
00:11:32,943 --> 00:11:35,315
It's a whole different story, isn't it?

158
00:11:36,113 --> 00:11:37,655
You're fired.

159
00:11:38,323 --> 00:11:41,360
Not a soul in this county isn't sick to death
of your bullshit.

160
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:46,241
Make yourself scarce and you'll make a lot
of people happy.

161
00:11:46,331 --> 00:11:47,956
- You little piss ant.
- Now...

162
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:49,073
...or later.

163
00:11:50,669 --> 00:11:52,911
You won't have any trouble finding me.

164
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,960
You're a dead man.

165
00:12:04,475 --> 00:12:07,475
Get the goddamn car.
We're going to Roderick's.

166
00:12:22,034 --> 00:12:23,196
<i>Boy...</i>

167
00:12:23,577 --> 00:12:25,570
<i>...another beer, please.</i>

168
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,908
Yeah,
that Buddy was a cool breeze.

169
00:12:32,961 --> 00:12:36,626
<i>Wade was known to put quite a few people</i>
<i>in the ground...</i>

170
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:39,877
<i>...and your daddy gets eyeball-to-eyeball</i>
<i>with him.</i>

171
00:12:40,886 --> 00:12:43,756
We made our pickup
at Roderick's place.

172
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:46,933
<i>Nobody's seen hide nor hair of him since.</i>

173
00:12:47,434 --> 00:12:52,013
He went missing the next day along
with $10,000 in county funds from the safe.

174
00:12:53,941 --> 00:12:55,732
<i>Never heard from him again.</i>

175
00:12:55,818 --> 00:12:58,854
Buddy Deeds said a thing,
he damn well backed it up.

176
00:12:59,905 --> 00:13:01,732
Never be another like him.

177
00:13:03,242 --> 00:13:07,370
So, I suppose then he arrested
all of Jimmy Herrera's people and...

178
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:09,447
...sent them back to the other side?

179
00:13:11,542 --> 00:13:13,618
He came to an accommodation.

180
00:13:14,795 --> 00:13:18,875
Money doesn't always have to change
hands to keep the wheels turning.

181
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:22,625
I know you had problems with your father.

182
00:13:23,554 --> 00:13:26,887
- And he and Muriel--
- Your mother was a saint.

183
00:13:28,058 --> 00:13:30,549
But Buddy Deeds was my salvation.

184
00:13:33,147 --> 00:13:35,186
Won't be another like him.

185
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:38,478
It is an honor for me...

186
00:13:38,569 --> 00:13:40,395
...to assume command of this unit.

187
00:13:40,487 --> 00:13:42,895
I look forward to working with all of you.

188
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:45,611
I'm sure you're all aware
of the Army's decision...

189
00:13:45,701 --> 00:13:47,409
<i>...to shut this post down.</i>

190
00:13:48,078 --> 00:13:50,996
<i>That doesn't mean, however,</i>
<i>that we're here to mark time...</i>

191
00:13:51,081 --> 00:13:52,789
...until we're reassigned.

192
00:13:53,625 --> 00:13:55,582
You may have heard rumors...

193
00:13:55,919 --> 00:13:58,208
<i>...that I run a very tight operation.</i>

194
00:13:58,922 --> 00:14:00,416
These rumors...

195
00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:02,424
...are not exaggerated.

196
00:16:04,214 --> 00:16:06,456
Somebody call a doctor!

197
00:16:13,182 --> 00:16:15,091
You weren't in here tonight, were you?

198
00:16:15,184 --> 00:16:16,346
No, no, sir.

199
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:17,971
Go out the back way.

200
00:16:18,061 --> 00:16:20,932
Somebody call a doctor!

201
00:16:24,443 --> 00:16:26,103
Tearing everything down.

202
00:16:26,195 --> 00:16:30,821
Our heritage, the memory of the people
who fought and died for this land.

203
00:16:30,908 --> 00:16:33,363
We fought and died for this land too.

204
00:16:33,577 --> 00:16:35,902
We fought the U.S. Army,
the Texas Rangers--

205
00:16:35,996 --> 00:16:37,538
Yeah, and you lost.

206
00:16:38,207 --> 00:16:40,413
Winners get the bragging rights.

207
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:45,495
People. It'd be best if we don't view this
in terms of winners and losers.

208
00:16:45,589 --> 00:16:48,424
The way she teaches,
she's got everything backward.

209
00:16:48,509 --> 00:16:50,631
I was on the textbook committee.
Her version--

210
00:16:51,053 --> 00:16:52,880
We think of the textbook...

211
00:16:52,971 --> 00:16:55,094
...as a guide, not as an absolute.

212
00:16:55,224 --> 00:16:57,928
It is not what we set as the standard.

213
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:02,271
Now, you people can believe
whatever you want...

214
00:17:02,356 --> 00:17:04,099
...but when it comes to teaching--

215
00:17:04,191 --> 00:17:08,319
They're our children too. As the majority
in this community, we have the right.

216
00:17:08,403 --> 00:17:13,398
The men who founded this state
have the right to have their story told.

217
00:17:13,617 --> 00:17:16,108
The men who founded this state
broke from Mexico.

218
00:17:16,203 --> 00:17:19,987
They needed slavery to be legal
to make a fortune in the cotton business.

219
00:17:20,082 --> 00:17:22,703
I think that's a bit of an oversimplification.

220
00:17:22,793 --> 00:17:26,376
- You reporting or running this meeting?
- Adding some historical perspective.

221
00:17:26,463 --> 00:17:28,752
You call it history, I call it propaganda.

222
00:17:28,841 --> 00:17:32,755
I'm sure they've got their own account
of the Alamo on the other side...

223
00:17:33,053 --> 00:17:35,971
<i>...but our schools shouldn't teach it</i>
<i>that way.</i>

224
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:37,219
Excuse me.

225
00:17:37,724 --> 00:17:42,719
I've only been trying to get across part
of the complexity of our situation here.

226
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:48,059
Cultures coming together
in both negative and positive ways.

227
00:17:48,443 --> 00:17:51,480
If you mean food and music and all,
I have no problem.

228
00:17:52,406 --> 00:17:53,948
<i>But when you start changing...</i>

229
00:17:54,032 --> 00:17:55,361
...who did what to who--

230
00:17:55,450 --> 00:17:58,866
We're just trying to present
a more complete picture.

231
00:17:59,246 --> 00:18:00,989
That's what's got to stop!

232
00:18:01,165 --> 00:18:05,577
There's enough ignorance in the world
without us encouraging it in school.

233
00:18:06,170 --> 00:18:08,839
Now, who are you calling ignorant?

234
00:18:09,256 --> 00:18:11,794
I hope the sucker dies.
Mess with me, that's what you get.

235
00:18:11,884 --> 00:18:13,923
Hospital says the kid is in bad shape.

236
00:18:14,011 --> 00:18:15,339
The shooter local?

237
00:18:15,429 --> 00:18:18,430
Houston. I think he knew the girl
from before.

238
00:18:18,765 --> 00:18:22,099
We'll take a statement from the GI's
before they go back to post.

239
00:18:22,186 --> 00:18:24,724
You can get the story from Otis.

240
00:18:25,314 --> 00:18:27,983
Any poop on the John Doe
we found today?

241
00:18:28,275 --> 00:18:32,439
No, nothing much.
Rangers put Ben Wetzel on it.

242
00:18:32,905 --> 00:18:34,399
I'll catch you later.

243
00:18:46,084 --> 00:18:48,575
He's only 15. He's about 5 foot 5--

244
00:18:48,754 --> 00:18:49,750
Pilar.

245
00:18:52,549 --> 00:18:53,878
Something wrong?

246
00:18:54,134 --> 00:18:55,628
They've got my son.

247
00:18:55,803 --> 00:18:56,716
Here?

248
00:18:56,887 --> 00:19:01,798
Somebody called about a house that was
broken into. They say they don't have--

249
00:19:02,643 --> 00:19:04,931
All right, I know what he looks like.

250
00:19:05,062 --> 00:19:06,770
I'll see what's going on.

251
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:11,098
I was....

252
00:19:13,529 --> 00:19:16,280
I was real sorry about Nando.

253
00:19:19,284 --> 00:19:20,909
He was a good fella.

254
00:19:25,123 --> 00:19:26,499
We haven't talked--

255
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:28,790
We haven't talked since high school.

256
00:19:30,754 --> 00:19:31,785
Yeah.

257
00:19:32,256 --> 00:19:33,964
I'll go check on your boy.

258
00:19:37,427 --> 00:19:41,259
Ritchie didn't say nothing,
'cause he didn't want to get in it.

259
00:19:41,598 --> 00:19:45,810
Then, next thing I know
there's shots and Ritchie's down.

260
00:19:47,896 --> 00:19:49,936
You got some boys you run in earlier?

261
00:19:52,651 --> 00:19:55,569
They tell me you're good at fixing things.

262
00:20:01,451 --> 00:20:03,943
Your father was a hell of a mechanic.

263
00:20:08,667 --> 00:20:11,240
You know, if you figure minimum wage...

264
00:20:11,336 --> 00:20:14,006
...on the time most thieves spend in jail...

265
00:20:14,214 --> 00:20:17,215
...they could have bought
most everything they stole.

266
00:20:17,718 --> 00:20:21,134
They asked me to hook it up for them.
I didn't steal anything.

267
00:20:21,722 --> 00:20:23,845
Well, I didn't say you did.

268
00:20:26,226 --> 00:20:28,385
My name's Sam, by the way.

269
00:20:31,273 --> 00:20:33,266
- He's all yours.
- Are you okay?

270
00:20:33,442 --> 00:20:35,434
What's the big deal?

271
00:20:35,527 --> 00:20:37,899
You'll find out when I get you home.

272
00:20:37,988 --> 00:20:39,151
Thanks, Sam.

273
00:20:39,490 --> 00:20:41,067
It's no problem.

274
00:20:43,577 --> 00:20:45,155
It was good seeing you again.

275
00:21:12,397 --> 00:21:15,766
Big O's is the only place
where African American soldiers...

276
00:21:15,859 --> 00:21:17,686
...feel comfortable, sir.

277
00:21:17,861 --> 00:21:21,230
- Have we had trouble there before?
- Fistfight now and then.

278
00:21:21,323 --> 00:21:24,490
- This town isn't much.
- They didn't come for a vacation.

279
00:21:24,576 --> 00:21:28,526
For many, it's their first time away
from home, dealing with new people....

280
00:21:28,622 --> 00:21:31,113
- I remember my first hitch--
- Substance abuse?

281
00:21:31,208 --> 00:21:34,078
Yes, sir, but I went through the program.
I haven't drunk--

282
00:21:34,169 --> 00:21:36,921
I meant on the post.
How are you dealing with it?

283
00:21:37,005 --> 00:21:39,710
We throw a urine test at them
once a month.

284
00:21:40,050 --> 00:21:41,509
Random numbers...

285
00:21:41,677 --> 00:21:43,586
...maybe 100 people at a time.

286
00:21:43,679 --> 00:21:46,715
- Let's make it once a week for a while.
- Yes, sir.

287
00:21:46,890 --> 00:21:50,888
I sprint the last quarter mile.
You don't have to keep up.

288
00:21:51,395 --> 00:21:52,723
Appreciate it, sir.

289
00:21:58,402 --> 00:22:00,774
Guy cracks walnuts with his asshole.

290
00:22:01,196 --> 00:22:03,521
You get the feeling
he doesn't want to be here?

291
00:23:01,757 --> 00:23:02,753
Sam the Man.

292
00:23:03,217 --> 00:23:05,921
Hey, Ben. Thanks for coming down.

293
00:23:08,180 --> 00:23:09,639
So, how's business?

294
00:23:10,307 --> 00:23:12,098
Business is booming.

295
00:23:12,684 --> 00:23:15,010
Got your drugs, got your illegals.

296
00:23:15,437 --> 00:23:19,601
Had a shooting the other night
at O's place. Soldier got ventilated.

297
00:23:20,108 --> 00:23:22,646
I hear they're closing Fort McKenzie.

298
00:23:22,736 --> 00:23:24,978
It'll pull a lot of jobs out of this county.

299
00:23:25,072 --> 00:23:29,449
We'll have folks swimming over to Mexico
to work in the sweat shops.

300
00:23:30,828 --> 00:23:32,488
Is that the word on our boy?

301
00:23:33,121 --> 00:23:34,450
This is Skinny.

302
00:23:35,207 --> 00:23:36,037
Skinny?

303
00:23:37,209 --> 00:23:39,961
When we find a body, it's Skinny or Stinky.

304
00:23:40,128 --> 00:23:42,536
Depends on how much meat's left
on the bones.

305
00:23:42,923 --> 00:23:44,547
That's a nice job.

306
00:23:45,634 --> 00:23:47,342
"A male Caucasian...

307
00:23:48,137 --> 00:23:49,928
"...40 to 60 years old...

308
00:23:50,013 --> 00:23:51,638
"...5 foot 9...

309
00:23:51,807 --> 00:23:53,266
<i>"...5 foot 11.</i>

310
00:23:53,976 --> 00:23:55,304
"Chewed tobacco."

311
00:23:55,394 --> 00:23:58,015
Then we'll get the dental records
and personal effects.

312
00:23:58,105 --> 00:23:59,729
It's Charlie Wade.

313
00:24:00,899 --> 00:24:02,014
That badge....

314
00:24:02,109 --> 00:24:04,516
- Didn't come out of a cereal box.
- No.

315
00:24:14,955 --> 00:24:18,289
You know the popular version
of how he left town.

316
00:24:18,709 --> 00:24:21,164
Everybody on the border knows that story.

317
00:24:21,545 --> 00:24:23,205
You got a cause of death?

318
00:24:23,297 --> 00:24:24,542
Skull was intact.

319
00:24:24,631 --> 00:24:27,087
No signs of trauma on what we found.

320
00:24:27,384 --> 00:24:29,044
Not much to go on.

321
00:24:29,928 --> 00:24:34,008
So, he could have gone out to the post,
just hopped the fence...

322
00:24:34,516 --> 00:24:36,723
...dug into the dirt on the rifle range...

323
00:24:36,810 --> 00:24:38,637
...and had a heart attack.

324
00:24:42,858 --> 00:24:46,143
You remember what old Buddy carried
for a side arm?

325
00:24:47,321 --> 00:24:48,696
Colt Peacemaker.

326
00:24:48,780 --> 00:24:49,895
.45.

327
00:24:49,990 --> 00:24:51,188
He swore by it.

328
00:24:54,119 --> 00:24:55,150
What?

329
00:24:56,246 --> 00:24:57,740
I was just wondering.

330
00:25:00,751 --> 00:25:02,743
Is Buddy on your short list?

331
00:25:02,961 --> 00:25:06,710
If it were some poor <i>majadero</i>
who swam across, got lost in the brush...

332
00:25:06,798 --> 00:25:10,084
...and starved out there
it wouldn't go much further, but...

333
00:25:10,385 --> 00:25:13,007
...this is a once prominent citizen
who disappeared.

334
00:25:13,388 --> 00:25:16,674
You've got to investigate.
There's no question about it.

335
00:25:17,601 --> 00:25:21,765
I'll keep names out of it until we get
some answers or hit a dead end.

336
00:25:22,648 --> 00:25:27,226
You know how the press is when they get
ahold of a murder story, even 40 years old.

337
00:25:28,987 --> 00:25:31,657
Yeah, yeah. They can do a number on you.

338
00:25:35,828 --> 00:25:37,203
I remember...

339
00:25:37,579 --> 00:25:40,948
...Charlie Wade come
to my father's hardware store once.

340
00:25:41,041 --> 00:25:42,749
I was just a little boy.

341
00:25:43,752 --> 00:25:46,243
I'd heard stories
about how he shot this one...

342
00:25:46,338 --> 00:25:48,295
...how he shot that one.

343
00:25:49,758 --> 00:25:51,502
The man winked at me.

344
00:25:52,261 --> 00:25:54,087
I peed my pants.

345
00:25:55,514 --> 00:25:56,842
Winked at me.

346
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:02,764
The fight against the Spanish,
a bloody conflict for dozens of years...

347
00:26:02,855 --> 00:26:06,140
<i>...till they are finally defeated in 1821...</i>

348
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:09,520
<i>...and Mexican independence is declared.</i>

349
00:26:09,862 --> 00:26:13,195
<i>Anglo settlers are invited</i>
<i>to colonize the area.</i>

350
00:26:13,365 --> 00:26:16,699
<i>By the time they begin the movement</i>
<i>against Santa Anna...</i>

351
00:26:16,869 --> 00:26:20,202
...they outnumber the Mexicans here
by four to one.

352
00:26:20,747 --> 00:26:24,745
The war between Mexico
and the anglo forces ends...

353
00:26:24,835 --> 00:26:26,662
...in 1836...

354
00:26:27,004 --> 00:26:31,048
<i>...with the formation</i>
<i>of the Texas republic. Texas...</i>

355
00:26:31,633 --> 00:26:33,293
...joins the United States...

356
00:26:33,385 --> 00:26:37,050
...as a state where slavery
is legal in 1845...

357
00:26:38,515 --> 00:26:42,216
<i>...after the so-called Mexican War,</i>
<i>then secedes to join...</i>

358
00:26:42,436 --> 00:26:46,683
...the Confederacy in 1861.
The Confederacy is beaten...

359
00:26:47,024 --> 00:26:50,808
...and the Reformation period here
is marked by range wars...

360
00:26:50,903 --> 00:26:53,061
...and race wars and all this...

361
00:26:53,447 --> 00:26:55,605
<i>...paralleled by the constant battles...</i>

362
00:26:55,699 --> 00:26:58,534
<i>...between the Mexican</i>
<i>and anglo settlers...</i>

363
00:26:58,744 --> 00:27:02,327
...and the various Indian nations.
What are we seeing here, Chet?

364
00:27:05,209 --> 00:27:07,664
Everybody's killing everybody else?

365
00:27:16,595 --> 00:27:18,801
I always wondered
what you mayors do...

366
00:27:18,889 --> 00:27:20,716
...when you're not cutting ribbons.

367
00:27:21,975 --> 00:27:23,090
Sam!

368
00:27:25,938 --> 00:27:26,969
Partner.

369
00:27:27,898 --> 00:27:29,772
You caught me playing hooky.

370
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:33,070
Floating around out here,
playing hell with them bass.

371
00:27:33,153 --> 00:27:35,062
Sounds great! Where do I sign up?

372
00:27:35,739 --> 00:27:38,230
You been by your old place lately?

373
00:27:38,534 --> 00:27:39,648
No.

374
00:27:39,743 --> 00:27:41,866
New people painted it some awful color.

375
00:27:43,914 --> 00:27:47,034
We found a body out
by Fort McKenzie yesterday.

376
00:27:47,626 --> 00:27:49,251
It'd been there a long time.

377
00:27:49,336 --> 00:27:51,744
Was it Davy Crockett or Jim Bowie?

378
00:27:55,717 --> 00:27:58,718
You recall if Charlie Wade was a Mason?

379
00:27:59,596 --> 00:28:00,592
Charlie?

380
00:28:01,265 --> 00:28:04,716
I believe he used to go for Lodge meetings
over to Laredo.

381
00:28:05,936 --> 00:28:08,688
What's Charlie Wade got to do
with your body?

382
00:28:09,398 --> 00:28:12,482
All he was wearing was
a big old Masonic ring...

383
00:28:12,609 --> 00:28:14,768
...and a Rio County sheriff's badge.

384
00:28:22,202 --> 00:28:25,322
You remember anything else
from the last night you saw him?

385
00:28:25,414 --> 00:28:28,165
I told the story enough times.

386
00:28:29,418 --> 00:28:33,629
We were in the car. He was stewing about
his fight with Buddy as we drove over...

387
00:28:33,714 --> 00:28:35,541
<i>...to Roderick Bledsoe's.</i>

388
00:28:35,799 --> 00:28:36,914
Bledsoe?

389
00:28:37,050 --> 00:28:39,376
He owned the colored roadhouse
before Otis.

390
00:28:39,470 --> 00:28:40,549
He's still living?

391
00:28:40,804 --> 00:28:41,967
No.

392
00:28:42,848 --> 00:28:46,893
I think his widow's still in their place
in Darktown, though.

393
00:28:48,479 --> 00:28:51,016
You think it was Charlie Wade, huh?

394
00:28:51,857 --> 00:28:53,896
Forensics people are sure of it.

395
00:28:56,153 --> 00:28:58,822
You got any idea
who might have put him there?

396
00:29:00,282 --> 00:29:02,239
Besides my father, I mean.

397
00:29:03,785 --> 00:29:05,944
There's no call for that, Sam.

398
00:29:06,663 --> 00:29:09,664
Wade made himself a pile of enemies
over the years.

399
00:29:10,125 --> 00:29:13,624
- Buddy was one of them.
- The dedication's tomorrow.

400
00:29:14,087 --> 00:29:16,792
It's a hell of a time
to bring up old business.

401
00:29:17,382 --> 00:29:21,546
People have made this whole big thing
around my father. If it's built on a crime...

402
00:29:21,637 --> 00:29:23,297
<i>...they deserve to know.</i>

403
00:29:23,847 --> 00:29:26,884
I understand why you might want
to believe he couldn't do it.

404
00:29:26,975 --> 00:29:30,095
I understand why you might want
to think he could.

405
00:29:38,946 --> 00:29:41,152
Thanks for your time, Hollis.

406
00:29:42,950 --> 00:29:44,278
Look at all this.

407
00:29:48,288 --> 00:29:49,747
Tackle, boat....

408
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:54,242
All just to catch a little old fish...

409
00:29:54,336 --> 00:29:57,622
...minding his own business
down at the bottom of the lake.

410
00:30:01,176 --> 00:30:03,963
Hardly seems worth the effort,
does it, Sam?

411
00:30:08,517 --> 00:30:10,842
You knew this young man before?

412
00:30:11,019 --> 00:30:14,020
From back in Houston.
We both come up off the street.

413
00:30:14,106 --> 00:30:16,395
Did you know
he'd be there last night?

414
00:30:16,483 --> 00:30:19,235
If I had, I wouldn't have gone in.

415
00:30:19,695 --> 00:30:21,983
And you
and Private Graves were....

416
00:30:22,197 --> 00:30:23,941
We were just dancing.

417
00:30:25,117 --> 00:30:26,991
We're not running a dating service.

418
00:30:27,077 --> 00:30:28,821
I know that, Sergeant.

419
00:30:28,912 --> 00:30:32,328
We were just dancing.
There was a bunch of us there.

420
00:30:32,583 --> 00:30:36,165
Shadow... just come down
looking for trouble.

421
00:30:37,421 --> 00:30:40,790
I don't like to get involved
with soldiers' personal lives...

422
00:30:41,008 --> 00:30:43,296
...but when it interferes with training....

423
00:30:43,385 --> 00:30:45,793
Shadow just gets crazy.

424
00:30:46,638 --> 00:30:49,639
Sergeant, how is Ritchie doing?
Private Graves?

425
00:30:50,225 --> 00:30:51,423
He'll live.

426
00:30:51,685 --> 00:30:53,559
He'll be transferred to Fort Sam...

427
00:30:53,645 --> 00:30:55,056
<i>...as soon as he's stabilized.</i>

428
00:30:55,147 --> 00:30:57,852
He'll probably be getting
a medical discharge.

429
00:31:00,110 --> 00:31:02,186
Will this go on my record?

430
00:31:03,530 --> 00:31:05,689
The incident will be noted.

431
00:31:06,241 --> 00:31:07,985
If it happened the way you say...

432
00:31:08,911 --> 00:31:11,069
<i>...there hasn't been an infraction.</i>

433
00:31:11,205 --> 00:31:12,699
Thank you, Sergeant.

434
00:31:13,081 --> 00:31:14,161
You're dismissed.

435
00:31:14,249 --> 00:31:15,874
Thank you, Sergeant.

436
00:31:27,137 --> 00:31:29,046
You spoil them, Cliff.

437
00:31:29,640 --> 00:31:33,009
- You don't believe her?
- That wasn't an interrogation.

438
00:31:33,101 --> 00:31:35,853
I'm in charge of her sorry ass and frankly--

439
00:31:35,938 --> 00:31:39,437
I won't give her the third-degree
because her ex-boyfriend's a thug.

440
00:31:39,525 --> 00:31:42,312
She's pulled herself out
of a rough neighborhood.

441
00:31:42,402 --> 00:31:46,068
And if she isn't careful,
she's gonna slide right back into it.

442
00:32:02,422 --> 00:32:03,833
Mrs. Bledsoe?

443
00:32:04,091 --> 00:32:05,253
That's me.

444
00:32:07,636 --> 00:32:09,261
I'm Sheriff Deeds.

445
00:32:10,973 --> 00:32:14,139
Sheriff Deeds is dead, honey.
You're just Sheriff Junior.

446
00:32:15,811 --> 00:32:18,136
Yeah, that's the story of my life.

447
00:32:18,730 --> 00:32:20,522
You ever play one of these?

448
00:32:23,652 --> 00:32:25,194
Yeah, I've seen them.

449
00:32:25,529 --> 00:32:27,984
Don't ever start up on them,
because...

450
00:32:28,073 --> 00:32:30,315
...once you do, you can't stop.

451
00:32:30,951 --> 00:32:35,328
I tell myself I'll just play
three little games after breakfast...

452
00:32:35,831 --> 00:32:37,491
...and here I am...

453
00:32:38,375 --> 00:32:40,415
...with half the day gone.

454
00:32:40,836 --> 00:32:43,623
May I ask you a few questions
about your husband?

455
00:32:44,381 --> 00:32:45,626
<i>Roderick.</i>

456
00:32:45,757 --> 00:32:48,379
I ain't gonna say nothing bad
about the man...

457
00:32:48,594 --> 00:32:50,467
...but you can ask away.

458
00:32:51,221 --> 00:32:53,344
He had the club on Old Trail Road.

459
00:32:53,474 --> 00:32:56,095
We run that club for over 20 years.

460
00:32:56,685 --> 00:32:59,010
Give it over to Otis Payne...

461
00:32:59,646 --> 00:33:02,137
...in 1967, April.

462
00:33:03,609 --> 00:33:05,601
You must remember Sheriff Wade.

463
00:33:05,944 --> 00:33:07,273
Them days...

464
00:33:08,113 --> 00:33:11,067
...you deal with Sheriff Wade
or you didn't deal.

465
00:33:11,450 --> 00:33:13,857
First of the month, every month...

466
00:33:13,952 --> 00:33:16,526
<i>...he'd remind you</i>
<i>who you really working for.</i>

467
00:33:17,915 --> 00:33:19,991
So, he squeezed money out of you?

468
00:33:20,751 --> 00:33:25,460
It wasn't legal to sell liquor in a glass
back then, unless you was a club, see?

469
00:33:27,508 --> 00:33:29,132
Roderick used to say:

470
00:33:29,468 --> 00:33:32,303
"Buy yourself a glass,
get a free membership."

471
00:33:34,264 --> 00:33:35,379
Sheriff Wade...

472
00:33:35,682 --> 00:33:38,008
...he could close you down anytime.

473
00:33:38,811 --> 00:33:40,518
And my father?

474
00:33:42,064 --> 00:33:44,140
Sheriff Buddy was a different story.

475
00:33:44,233 --> 00:33:48,480
As long as Roderick throw his weight
the right way at election day...

476
00:33:48,904 --> 00:33:52,818
<i>...make sure all the colored come to vote,</i>
<i>throw a barbecue for the right folks....</i>

477
00:33:52,908 --> 00:33:55,316
Sheriff Buddy kept to his word.

478
00:33:55,953 --> 00:33:57,910
That Sheriff Wade, though...

479
00:33:59,122 --> 00:34:00,747
...he could get ugly.

480
00:34:02,167 --> 00:34:03,792
People didn't complain?

481
00:34:04,795 --> 00:34:07,120
Not if you was colored or Mexican.

482
00:34:07,339 --> 00:34:09,497
Not if you wanted to keep breathing.

483
00:34:09,758 --> 00:34:13,092
I remember the last time I seen him
before he gone missing.

484
00:34:13,178 --> 00:34:15,467
He come fussing around our place.

485
00:34:15,806 --> 00:34:18,511
He used to come in
whilst we was in full swing.

486
00:34:19,184 --> 00:34:21,509
<i>Making everybody nervous.</i>

487
00:34:21,854 --> 00:34:24,771
<i>Had him a smile like the Grim Reaper.</i>

488
00:34:25,315 --> 00:34:28,352
<i>He used to sit there</i>
<i>with his hand on his old gun...</i>

489
00:34:28,443 --> 00:34:31,195
<i>...acting the kingfish with everybody.</i>

490
00:34:35,200 --> 00:34:36,481
<i>Otis Payne come...</i>

491
00:34:36,577 --> 00:34:38,818
<i>...to work for us about that time...</i>

492
00:34:40,205 --> 00:34:43,657
<i>...and that boy had him some attitude.</i>

493
00:35:03,687 --> 00:35:04,683
Pour it.

494
00:35:06,190 --> 00:35:07,185
What?

495
00:35:07,858 --> 00:35:08,854
Pour it.

496
00:35:21,330 --> 00:35:22,409
I know you?

497
00:35:22,498 --> 00:35:23,743
Name's Otis.

498
00:35:24,750 --> 00:35:25,995
Otis what?

499
00:35:27,711 --> 00:35:28,742
Payne.

500
00:35:29,755 --> 00:35:31,166
They call me "O."

501
00:35:32,382 --> 00:35:34,042
One of Cleroe Payne's boys?

502
00:35:35,803 --> 00:35:37,961
I sent your daddy to the farm once.

503
00:35:39,723 --> 00:35:41,098
Yeah, I know that.

504
00:35:41,558 --> 00:35:43,218
Why you think that was?

505
00:35:45,020 --> 00:35:48,389
Some crop needed picking
and the man was short-handed.

506
00:35:49,817 --> 00:35:53,232
As I remember, it was 'cause
he had a sassy mouth on him.

507
00:35:53,403 --> 00:35:54,862
<i>Must run in the family.</i>

508
00:35:56,073 --> 00:35:58,611
You wouldn't be running numbers
out of this club?

509
00:36:00,661 --> 00:36:02,784
Running numbers is illegal, sir.

510
00:36:03,038 --> 00:36:07,285
Running numbers without I knowin'
about it is both illegal and unhealthy.

511
00:36:07,668 --> 00:36:09,078
You remember that.

512
00:36:11,296 --> 00:36:13,004
<i>Son, you're not finished.</i>

513
00:36:13,257 --> 00:36:14,371
Pour his.

514
00:36:15,092 --> 00:36:16,467
I prefer it in the bottle.

515
00:36:16,552 --> 00:36:17,927
Shut up, Hollis.

516
00:36:24,226 --> 00:36:25,969
How come you don't look familiar?

517
00:36:26,603 --> 00:36:28,560
I've been away, up in Houston.

518
00:36:29,398 --> 00:36:30,429
Houston?

519
00:36:30,691 --> 00:36:33,229
I hear they let you boys run wild up there.

520
00:36:34,069 --> 00:36:35,777
Look what you've done now.

521
00:36:36,071 --> 00:36:38,443
Better get something to wipe it up, son.

522
00:36:43,036 --> 00:36:45,574
You spilled it.
Maybe you should wipe it up.

523
00:36:53,589 --> 00:36:57,752
I told you to do something. Will you hop
to it or will we have a problem?

524
00:37:01,263 --> 00:37:04,217
You don't want to turn tail
in front of your people?

525
00:37:04,308 --> 00:37:05,683
I understand.

526
00:37:09,771 --> 00:37:12,097
Come on, Houston, give it a try.

527
00:37:12,608 --> 00:37:13,853
Come to Papa.

528
00:37:16,236 --> 00:37:17,517
Don't mind him.

529
00:37:17,613 --> 00:37:21,361
He's a bit slow, is all.
He don't mean nothing by it.

530
00:37:22,534 --> 00:37:24,112
That the problem, son?

531
00:37:24,411 --> 00:37:25,442
You slow?

532
00:37:26,455 --> 00:37:27,201
Otis!

533
00:37:28,081 --> 00:37:29,624
Apologize to the sheriff.

534
00:37:32,044 --> 00:37:34,795
Sheriff, you got him too scared to peep.

535
00:37:35,631 --> 00:37:37,623
Maybe if you'd put that gun up.

536
00:37:38,217 --> 00:37:39,627
You telling me what to do?

537
00:37:39,718 --> 00:37:41,509
No, Sheriff, I'm just....

538
00:37:41,637 --> 00:37:43,297
Is that whisky in them glasses?

539
00:37:45,516 --> 00:37:48,635
I'll have to cite you
for violation of a state law.

540
00:37:49,144 --> 00:37:51,635
This is a club, Sheriff. You've been here.

541
00:37:52,064 --> 00:37:54,733
You people better clear out of here now!

542
00:38:03,492 --> 00:38:05,615
Learn how to act your place, son.

543
00:38:07,329 --> 00:38:08,788
This isn't Houston.

544
00:38:13,460 --> 00:38:15,951
'Course, I was young...

545
00:38:16,964 --> 00:38:18,956
...and full of beans back then.

546
00:38:20,133 --> 00:38:24,380
I didn't understand the spot
I was putting Roderick in.

547
00:38:30,769 --> 00:38:33,723
And that was the last time you saw him?

548
00:38:35,440 --> 00:38:38,110
I think he came in one more time...

549
00:38:39,486 --> 00:38:41,230
...with Hollis and....

550
00:38:41,822 --> 00:38:44,028
No, no, your daddy wasn't with him.

551
00:38:44,283 --> 00:38:46,441
Made their monthly pickup.

552
00:38:47,161 --> 00:38:51,657
Roderick wasn't in, so I kept my mouth
shut and handed over that envelope.

553
00:38:52,916 --> 00:38:54,708
That was the night he disappeared?

554
00:38:57,171 --> 00:38:58,499
Could have been.

555
00:39:06,221 --> 00:39:07,502
You own a gun?

556
00:39:08,682 --> 00:39:09,595
Back then?

557
00:39:10,517 --> 00:39:11,596
No.

558
00:39:12,978 --> 00:39:14,141
How about Roderick?

559
00:39:14,980 --> 00:39:16,260
Oh, he kept...

560
00:39:17,691 --> 00:39:22,187
...a big old piece back behind the bar,
just so folks knew it was there.

561
00:39:23,197 --> 00:39:25,189
I don't keep one here now.

562
00:39:25,908 --> 00:39:27,781
Don't much care for them.

563
00:39:29,411 --> 00:39:31,404
And when my father was sheriff?

564
00:39:31,705 --> 00:39:32,903
What about him?

565
00:39:32,998 --> 00:39:34,741
What was your deal with him?

566
00:39:40,923 --> 00:39:43,758
Buddy was more part of the big picture:

567
00:39:45,093 --> 00:39:47,216
County political machine...

568
00:39:47,930 --> 00:39:50,599
...Chamber of Commerce, zoning Board....

569
00:39:52,267 --> 00:39:56,099
If I kept those people happy,
he was pretty much on my side.

570
00:39:56,563 --> 00:40:01,439
When somebody thought of starting up
a new bar for the black folks, they'd be....

571
00:40:03,403 --> 00:40:05,230
How should I say this?

572
00:40:05,656 --> 00:40:08,111
They'd be officially discouraged.

573
00:40:09,827 --> 00:40:11,819
He ever accept cash for a favor?

574
00:40:19,711 --> 00:40:23,163
I don't recall a prisoner ever died...

575
00:40:23,590 --> 00:40:25,583
...in your daddy's custody.

576
00:40:27,094 --> 00:40:29,383
I don't recall a man in this county...

577
00:40:29,596 --> 00:40:31,719
...black, white, Mexican...

578
00:40:32,683 --> 00:40:35,174
...who'd hesitate for a minute...

579
00:40:35,811 --> 00:40:39,511
...before they'd call on Buddy Deeds
to solve a problem.

580
00:40:40,899 --> 00:40:42,393
More than that...

581
00:40:44,153 --> 00:40:45,896
...I wouldn't care to say.

582
00:40:48,574 --> 00:40:51,824
I'm supposed to tell my friends
they're too low-class to hang with?

583
00:40:51,910 --> 00:40:52,906
Come on, Amado.

584
00:40:53,245 --> 00:40:55,072
'Cause I'm not like Miss Honor Roll?

585
00:40:55,164 --> 00:40:56,824
Leave your sister out of it.

586
00:40:56,915 --> 00:40:58,991
You and those teachers in that dump....

587
00:40:59,084 --> 00:41:01,456
<i>Your story's over, so nobody can have fun.</i>

588
00:41:01,545 --> 00:41:02,494
You jerk.

589
00:41:02,588 --> 00:41:04,497
You have no friends.

590
00:41:04,590 --> 00:41:06,666
Who'd be friends with a <i>pachuco</i> wannabe?

591
00:41:07,050 --> 00:41:09,257
I don't pretend I came on the Mayflower.

592
00:41:09,344 --> 00:41:10,969
And those stupid girls.

593
00:41:11,054 --> 00:41:12,169
Shut up.

594
00:41:12,264 --> 00:41:15,763
Joanie Orozco's telling the whole school
she's in love with Santo Guerra.

595
00:41:15,851 --> 00:41:16,764
So?

596
00:41:16,852 --> 00:41:19,425
You can't be desperately in love
when you're 14.

597
00:41:20,355 --> 00:41:22,562
<i>Not if you have half a brain in your head.</i>

598
00:41:22,649 --> 00:41:24,309
Of course, you can.

599
00:41:24,943 --> 00:41:25,857
What?

600
00:41:26,320 --> 00:41:29,071
It's got nothing to do with being smart.

601
00:41:30,032 --> 00:41:32,605
It's ancient goddamn history, Danny.

602
00:41:32,784 --> 00:41:36,616
1963, they dam up the north branch
to make Lake Pescadero...

603
00:41:36,705 --> 00:41:38,698
...and a whole town disappears.

604
00:41:38,790 --> 00:41:40,035
A squatter's town!

605
00:41:40,125 --> 00:41:44,621
People lived in Perdido for over 100 years!
Mexicans and Chicanos are deported...

606
00:41:44,713 --> 00:41:48,580
...forcibly evicted by our local hero,
Buddy Deeds, and his department.

607
00:41:48,759 --> 00:41:50,965
There was a bill from the state legislature.

608
00:41:51,053 --> 00:41:54,303
Families were split apart!
A whole community was destroyed!

609
00:41:54,431 --> 00:41:58,760
And who gets Lakefront property
bought for a fraction of the market price?

610
00:41:59,102 --> 00:42:03,100
Buddy Deeds, Sheriff of Rio County,
and his Chief Deputy, Hollis Pogue.

611
00:42:03,899 --> 00:42:05,274
Are you finished?

612
00:42:06,735 --> 00:42:08,609
Look, I'm not after you, Sam.

613
00:42:09,029 --> 00:42:12,647
I just think people ought to know
the full story on Buddy Deeds.

614
00:42:15,118 --> 00:42:16,661
That makes two of us.

615
00:42:20,791 --> 00:42:25,085
What's the big deal? Go back over,
talk to the man, and bury the hatchet.

616
00:42:25,170 --> 00:42:28,539
Why me? He's had almost 40 years
and I haven't heard from him.

617
00:42:28,632 --> 00:42:30,091
He was probably embarrassed.

618
00:42:30,175 --> 00:42:33,461
Otis Payne was never embarrassed
about a thing in his life.

619
00:42:33,720 --> 00:42:35,594
You were 8 when he left.

620
00:42:35,848 --> 00:42:39,051
He moved three houses down
with my mother's best friend.

621
00:42:39,601 --> 00:42:40,681
Dad.

622
00:42:41,395 --> 00:42:43,637
"Delmore, where's your daddy?"

623
00:42:43,772 --> 00:42:47,437
Godforsaken town.
Everybody in everybody else's business.

624
00:42:47,651 --> 00:42:49,394
Everybody loved Otis. Big "O."

625
00:42:49,486 --> 00:42:52,736
Always there with a smile or a loan...

626
00:42:52,823 --> 00:42:55,740
- ...or a free drink.
- Dad, can I talk to you about track?

627
00:42:55,826 --> 00:42:56,822
People change.

628
00:42:57,411 --> 00:42:58,609
Not that much.

629
00:42:58,704 --> 00:42:59,700
I talked to the coach.

630
00:42:59,788 --> 00:43:02,077
I told you. Next year,
if your grades are high.

631
00:43:02,166 --> 00:43:03,411
I have a B average!

632
00:43:03,500 --> 00:43:06,287
How many B students do you think
they take at West Point?

633
00:43:06,378 --> 00:43:08,869
We'll be here for three years.
We'll have to see him.

634
00:43:09,548 --> 00:43:10,579
No, we don't.

635
00:43:20,684 --> 00:43:23,804
Get off the phone.
We've got a big wedding.

636
00:43:24,062 --> 00:43:24,976
Mommy....

637
00:43:29,401 --> 00:43:31,726
They are getting stupider
every year.

638
00:43:31,820 --> 00:43:34,192
Maybe you're getting less patient.

639
00:43:34,781 --> 00:43:38,115
If they're going to survive,
they have to know how to work.

640
00:43:38,494 --> 00:43:41,067
You hire illegals,
what do you expect?

641
00:43:41,663 --> 00:43:43,656
Nobody's illegal in my cafe!

642
00:43:44,041 --> 00:43:47,623
They've got green cards,
relatives who were born here.

643
00:43:48,045 --> 00:43:50,915
If they only had a little common sense,
I'd be happy.

644
00:43:51,006 --> 00:43:54,126
If you took more time training them,
you wouldn't have to--

645
00:43:54,218 --> 00:43:57,717
Did you come here to teach me
how to run my business?

646
00:44:05,813 --> 00:44:07,935
Do you want to take a trip...

647
00:44:08,065 --> 00:44:09,559
<i>...down south with us?</i>

648
00:44:09,650 --> 00:44:11,726
<i>Maybe see where you grew up?</i>

649
00:44:12,194 --> 00:44:13,605
Why would I want to go there?

650
00:44:13,695 --> 00:44:15,154
You must be curious...

651
00:44:15,239 --> 00:44:19,153
...how it's changed. Amado is
into this big <i>tejano</i>-roots thing...

652
00:44:20,661 --> 00:44:23,365
<i>...and I've never been further</i>
<i>than Ciudad Leön</i>.

653
00:44:23,580 --> 00:44:25,288
You want to see Mexicans?

654
00:44:25,457 --> 00:44:27,580
Open your eyes and look around you.

655
00:44:27,876 --> 00:44:29,833
We're up to our ears in them.

656
00:44:31,922 --> 00:44:33,250
Mommy...

657
00:44:35,175 --> 00:44:37,880
...how old were you when my father died?

658
00:44:38,846 --> 00:44:40,221
He was killed.

659
00:44:40,848 --> 00:44:42,639
Right, when he was killed.

660
00:44:44,393 --> 00:44:46,966
A little older than Paloma is now.

661
00:44:47,896 --> 00:44:49,805
How come you never remarried?

662
00:44:51,483 --> 00:44:53,476
It just didn't happen.

663
00:44:55,070 --> 00:44:56,399
<i>There must have been...</i>

664
00:44:56,488 --> 00:44:57,651
...somebody.

665
00:44:59,116 --> 00:45:00,575
I was too busy.

666
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:05,196
Nobody is too busy.

667
00:45:05,831 --> 00:45:06,910
Maybe now.

668
00:45:07,207 --> 00:45:09,330
It was different back then.

669
00:45:09,835 --> 00:45:12,836
I had to do all the shopping,
all the cooking....

670
00:45:13,172 --> 00:45:17,169
What do I need some <i>chulo</i> with grease
under his nails to drink up the profit?

671
00:45:18,343 --> 00:45:19,257
Thank you.

672
00:45:19,553 --> 00:45:20,833
I don't mean Fernando.

673
00:45:22,222 --> 00:45:24,892
When I brought him home,
those were your exact words:

674
00:45:24,975 --> 00:45:27,051
"A <i>chulo</i> with grease under his nails."

675
00:45:27,144 --> 00:45:28,306
I never said that.

676
00:45:28,395 --> 00:45:31,230
You made it pretty damn clear.
You thought he was nobody.

677
00:45:32,191 --> 00:45:34,230
I thought you could do better.

678
00:45:34,401 --> 00:45:35,895
What? What?

679
00:45:37,237 --> 00:45:40,772
Become a nun? You didn't even want me
to go out with anglos.

680
00:45:40,866 --> 00:45:43,404
I never said that. Just that boy.

681
00:45:44,578 --> 00:45:45,906
"That boy."

682
00:45:47,164 --> 00:45:49,406
Say his name, for Christ's sake.

683
00:45:52,586 --> 00:45:54,994
You people are stealing from me.

684
00:46:02,221 --> 00:46:04,012
<i>Is she your mother?</i>

685
00:46:06,099 --> 00:46:07,510
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

686
00:46:07,851 --> 00:46:10,521
Now, I'm as liberal as the next guy.

687
00:46:10,854 --> 00:46:13,061
If the next guy is a redneck.

688
00:46:13,899 --> 00:46:15,358
But I got to say...

689
00:46:15,943 --> 00:46:19,228
...I think there's something
to this cold-climate business.

690
00:46:19,613 --> 00:46:22,104
I mean, you go to the beach...

691
00:46:22,574 --> 00:46:23,950
...what do you do?

692
00:46:25,077 --> 00:46:28,944
Drink a few beers, wait for that fish
to flop up on the sand.

693
00:46:29,289 --> 00:46:32,207
You can't build no civilization that way.

694
00:46:33,210 --> 00:46:35,499
But you got a cold winter coming on...

695
00:46:35,796 --> 00:46:37,420
...you got to plan ahead.

696
00:46:37,506 --> 00:46:40,127
That gives your old cerebral cortex
a workout.

697
00:46:40,217 --> 00:46:42,625
Good thing you were born down here then.

698
00:46:44,304 --> 00:46:47,756
You joke about it, Sam,
but we are in a state of crisis.

699
00:46:48,267 --> 00:46:51,137
<i>The lines of demarcation are getting fuzzy.</i>

700
00:46:51,353 --> 00:46:55,351
To run a successful civilization, you've got
to have your lines of demarcation...

701
00:46:55,440 --> 00:46:58,644
...between right and wrong,
this one and that one.

702
00:46:59,361 --> 00:47:00,820
Your daddy understood that.

703
00:47:00,904 --> 00:47:02,897
<i>He was.... What do you call it?</i>

704
00:47:03,699 --> 00:47:07,032
The referee in this damn <i>menudo</i>
we got down here.

705
00:47:07,494 --> 00:47:12,489
He understood how most folks don't want
their salt and sugar in the same jar.

706
00:47:13,584 --> 00:47:14,829
If you mixed drinks...

707
00:47:14,918 --> 00:47:16,745
...as bad as you mix metaphors...

708
00:47:16,837 --> 00:47:18,580
<i>...you'd be out of a job.</i>

709
00:47:18,922 --> 00:47:21,793
You're the last white sheriff
this town will see.

710
00:47:22,009 --> 00:47:26,137
Hollis retires next year.
Jorge Guerra will take over.

711
00:47:26,597 --> 00:47:28,673
This is it, right here, Sam.

712
00:47:29,141 --> 00:47:34,052
This bar is the last stand.
<i>Se habla</i> American, goddamn it!

713
00:47:35,355 --> 00:47:37,929
And even in here, it's sliding away.

714
00:47:39,651 --> 00:47:42,059
Take that pair over there in the corner.

715
00:47:44,031 --> 00:47:46,818
A place like this, 20 years ago...

716
00:47:47,868 --> 00:47:51,403
...Buddy'd been on them.
He'd have went over there...

717
00:47:51,497 --> 00:47:53,323
<i>...and given them a warning.</i>

718
00:47:53,499 --> 00:47:57,496
Not that he had it in for the colored,
but just as a kind of a safety tip.

719
00:47:59,588 --> 00:48:01,296
Yeah, bet he would.

720
00:48:02,508 --> 00:48:04,168
The day that man died...

721
00:48:05,594 --> 00:48:08,002
...they broke the goddamn mold.

722
00:48:14,812 --> 00:48:16,851
- Seriously.
- Seriously?

723
00:48:17,189 --> 00:48:19,098
I think we should get married.

724
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:22,060
We've been through this before.

725
00:48:22,152 --> 00:48:23,563
We should just do it.

726
00:48:23,654 --> 00:48:27,354
And if I get transferred to another post?
Germany or Korea?

727
00:48:27,783 --> 00:48:29,325
I'd ask for a transfer too.

728
00:48:29,409 --> 00:48:31,402
Which they'd most likely turn down.

729
00:48:31,495 --> 00:48:33,820
I'd quit the Army for you, if it came to that.

730
00:48:35,374 --> 00:48:37,201
You know, you are something.

731
00:48:37,543 --> 00:48:41,410
Man's going to retire in two years
and he offers to quit.

732
00:48:41,630 --> 00:48:43,255
Big goddamn deal.

733
00:48:43,966 --> 00:48:45,080
Excuse me.

734
00:48:45,425 --> 00:48:46,421
Sheriff.

735
00:48:47,136 --> 00:48:48,713
This is Sergeant....

736
00:48:49,054 --> 00:48:51,011
This is Priscilla Worth.

737
00:48:51,306 --> 00:48:54,224
Sheriff Deeds was with us
on our archeological find.

738
00:48:54,393 --> 00:48:56,385
They're building a shopping mall there?

739
00:48:57,187 --> 00:49:00,603
If certain people have their way,
it's gonna be a new jail.

740
00:49:01,316 --> 00:49:04,353
They're closing down military
and putting up jails...

741
00:49:04,444 --> 00:49:05,903
<i>...like 7-11 stores.</i>

742
00:49:07,865 --> 00:49:11,945
Do either of you have any idea
when they stopped using that site...

743
00:49:12,035 --> 00:49:13,530
<i>...as a rifle range?</i>

744
00:49:14,204 --> 00:49:16,363
Fort McKenzie stopped training infantry...

745
00:49:16,456 --> 00:49:20,122
<i>...there in the late '50s. It was just</i>
<i>a playground for the jackrabbits...</i>

746
