01:09:37,423 --> 01:09:39,914
It was for personal consumption.

997
01:09:40,426 --> 01:09:43,297
You going to smoke an acre and a half
of marijuana?

998
01:09:44,096 --> 01:09:47,216
I got a bad stomach.
It helps me to digest.

999
01:09:47,308 --> 01:09:49,680
Your father never bothered me about it.

1000
01:09:50,061 --> 01:09:54,390
Leastways not till the drug people
got on his case in the late '60s.

1001
01:09:55,107 --> 01:09:57,777
I thought he busted you
a couple of times.

1002
01:09:57,943 --> 01:09:58,939
No.

1003
01:09:59,528 --> 01:10:00,904
Different charge.

1004
01:10:01,530 --> 01:10:02,941
I had a still.

1005
01:10:03,366 --> 01:10:06,616
Made my own mescal.
That's how come I ruined my stomach.

1006
01:10:07,161 --> 01:10:09,486
I'm surprised he bothered with it.

1007
01:10:09,580 --> 01:10:11,786
He was afraid I'd poison somebody.

1008
01:10:13,918 --> 01:10:16,325
Your father tried to do good for people.

1009
01:10:16,671 --> 01:10:18,497
- So I've heard.
- And your mother...

1010
01:10:18,589 --> 01:10:20,048
...she was a saint.

1011
01:10:20,675 --> 01:10:23,248
Remember that summer I built that patio
at your house?

1012
01:10:23,344 --> 01:10:25,633
She made me lunch every day.

1013
01:10:26,847 --> 01:10:28,342
You were working there.

1014
01:10:28,432 --> 01:10:31,303
It could have been another box lunch
from the jail.

1015
01:10:32,311 --> 01:10:35,645
So you built our patio
while you were on the county?

1016
01:10:36,065 --> 01:10:40,063
Out in the fresh air?
Nice gringo lady making you pies?

1017
01:10:40,236 --> 01:10:42,275
Who'd sit in that jail cell all day?

1018
01:10:44,156 --> 01:10:47,442
Sheriff Buddy, man.
<i>There's no one like him.</i>

1019
01:10:47,660 --> 01:10:50,365
After that <i>cabrön</i>, Charlie Wade.

1020
01:10:50,454 --> 01:10:53,028
I heard Wade was a bit tough
on the Mexicans.

1021
01:10:57,795 --> 01:11:01,164
He murdered Eladio Cruz.
Is that tough enough for you?

1022
01:11:03,592 --> 01:11:04,837
Murdered him?

1023
01:11:05,011 --> 01:11:07,846
Chucho Montoya saw it with his own eyes.

1024
01:11:09,473 --> 01:11:11,098
Shot him in cold blood.

1025
01:11:11,183 --> 01:11:13,757
<i>Charlie Wade was a big asshole.</i>

1026
01:11:14,812 --> 01:11:15,761
Sam....

1027
01:11:18,691 --> 01:11:19,722
Wait up.

1028
01:11:24,447 --> 01:11:25,692
You're out early.

1029
01:11:27,241 --> 01:11:30,195
Haven't seen much of you at the jail lately.

1030
01:11:30,369 --> 01:11:32,611
Well, I'm working on a few things.

1031
01:11:33,205 --> 01:11:35,696
I'm going over to the other side.

1032
01:11:36,709 --> 01:11:37,989
Republicans?

1033
01:11:38,210 --> 01:11:39,705
No, Mexico.

1034
01:11:40,755 --> 01:11:42,546
Got to talk to someone.

1035
01:11:43,132 --> 01:11:44,875
They got telephones.

1036
01:11:45,051 --> 01:11:45,999
No.

1037
01:11:46,344 --> 01:11:48,087
It's got to be in person.

1038
01:11:51,307 --> 01:11:52,421
Sam, I....

1039
01:11:55,186 --> 01:11:56,561
The Committee....

1040
01:11:57,146 --> 01:11:59,637
Jorge and Fenton and all, they...

1041
01:12:00,232 --> 01:12:01,608
...they've asked me--

1042
01:12:01,692 --> 01:12:04,148
They want you to stand for sheriff
next election.

1043
01:12:05,780 --> 01:12:06,775
Yeah.

1044
01:12:08,407 --> 01:12:09,901
You'd do a good job.

1045
01:12:11,452 --> 01:12:12,483
Thanks.

1046
01:12:13,788 --> 01:12:15,068
What about you?

1047
01:12:15,706 --> 01:12:17,699
I don't know if I'll still want it.

1048
01:12:21,545 --> 01:12:24,036
I just didn't want to go around your back.

1049
01:12:24,173 --> 01:12:25,964
I appreciate you telling me.

1050
01:12:29,387 --> 01:12:30,964
You think we need a new jail?

1051
01:12:34,558 --> 01:12:35,934
Well, Sam....

1052
01:12:37,061 --> 01:12:39,219
It's a complicated issue.

1053
01:12:41,440 --> 01:12:42,603
Yeah, Ray.

1054
01:12:43,985 --> 01:12:46,061
You'd be a hell of a sheriff.

1055
01:13:39,749 --> 01:13:40,828
Down here...

1056
01:13:40,916 --> 01:13:43,917
<i>...we don't throw everything away</i>
<i>like you gringos do.</i>

1057
01:13:46,047 --> 01:13:47,624
Recycling, right?

1058
01:13:49,383 --> 01:13:50,961
We invented that.

1059
01:13:51,761 --> 01:13:54,631
The government doesn't have
to tell people to do it.

1060
01:13:57,141 --> 01:13:59,098
You own this place, huh?

1061
01:14:00,978 --> 01:14:02,354
This place...

1062
01:14:02,647 --> 01:14:04,639
...the one across the street...

1063
01:14:05,566 --> 01:14:08,140
...three or four others in Ciudad León.

1064
01:14:12,782 --> 01:14:14,406
"King of the Tires."

1065
01:14:16,494 --> 01:14:20,408
A lot of your people rolling over that bridge
on my rubber.

1066
01:14:20,873 --> 01:14:23,079
You lived in the States for a while?

1067
01:14:24,001 --> 01:14:24,997
Fifteen years.

1068
01:14:25,795 --> 01:14:27,621
Made some money, came back here?

1069
01:14:29,507 --> 01:14:30,835
Something like that.

1070
01:14:31,884 --> 01:14:35,467
Hey, you ever know
a fella named Eladio Cruz?

1071
01:14:38,516 --> 01:14:41,007
You're the sheriff of Rio County, right?

1072
01:14:55,658 --> 01:14:57,282
Step across this line.

1073
01:15:04,709 --> 01:15:07,330
You're not the sheriff of nothing anymore.

1074
01:15:08,337 --> 01:15:12,631
Just some <i>tejano</i> with a lot of questions
I don't have to answer.

1075
01:15:13,676 --> 01:15:15,253
<i>A bird flying south...</i>

1076
01:15:16,137 --> 01:15:18,129
...you think he sees this line?

1077
01:15:18,848 --> 01:15:21,006
Rattlesnake, <i>jabalina</i>...

1078
01:15:22,018 --> 01:15:23,512
...whatever you got.

1079
01:15:24,478 --> 01:15:28,143
You think halfway across that line
they start thinking different?

1080
01:15:28,733 --> 01:15:30,357
Why should a man?

1081
01:15:31,402 --> 01:15:34,438
Your government's been pretty happy
to have that line.

1082
01:15:35,364 --> 01:15:37,855
The question's just been where to draw it.

1083
01:15:43,164 --> 01:15:46,118
My government can go fuck itself
and so can yours.

1084
01:15:48,127 --> 01:15:50,285
I'm talking about people here.

1085
01:15:50,463 --> 01:15:51,494
Men.

1086
01:15:58,012 --> 01:15:59,387
Eladio Cruz...

1087
01:16:00,264 --> 01:16:03,929
<i>...is giving his friends a lift one day</i>
<i>in his</i> camión.

1088
01:16:04,185 --> 01:16:07,767
<i>But since they're on one side</i>
<i>of this invisible line and not the other...</i>

1089
01:16:07,855 --> 01:16:10,690
<i>...they got to hide</i>
<i>in the back</i> como criminales.

1090
01:16:10,941 --> 01:16:14,773
<i>And because over there</i>
<i>he's just another Mex</i> bracero...

1091
01:16:14,987 --> 01:16:17,194
<i>...any man with a badge is his</i> jefe.

1092
01:16:22,828 --> 01:16:23,943
CHUCHO:

1093
01:17:28,352 --> 01:17:29,681
What's in the back?

1094
01:17:29,770 --> 01:17:32,392
Not much, <i>jefe</i>. Some watermelons.

1095
01:17:32,940 --> 01:17:34,980
I'm driving them up to the market.

1096
01:17:35,067 --> 01:17:37,024
They could bring a good price.

1097
01:17:40,489 --> 01:17:43,490
I heard somebody's been
hauling wets on this road.

1098
01:17:44,952 --> 01:17:47,194
I haven't seen anybody doing that.

1099
01:17:48,789 --> 01:17:51,245
That person's been bragging
all over the county...

1100
01:17:51,334 --> 01:17:54,749
...how he doesn't have to cut
that gringo sheriff in on it.

1101
01:17:54,879 --> 01:17:57,251
Run his own operation without any help.

1102
01:17:58,799 --> 01:18:00,128
<i>What's your name?</i>

1103
01:18:00,801 --> 01:18:02,082
Eladio Cruz.

1104
01:18:04,096 --> 01:18:07,050
You know this road's got a bad reputation.

1105
01:18:07,683 --> 01:18:08,928
Reputation?

1106
01:18:09,101 --> 01:18:10,761
<i>Bandidos</i>, Injuns.

1107
01:18:12,104 --> 01:18:15,853
Many an unfortunate soul
has been ambushed out on this stretch.

1108
01:18:15,941 --> 01:18:18,267
I hope you're carrying some protection.

1109
01:18:18,486 --> 01:18:19,766
Protection?

1110
01:18:20,988 --> 01:18:23,111
You carrying a firearm, son?

1111
01:18:23,574 --> 01:18:24,985
Don't lie to me now.

1112
01:18:28,162 --> 01:18:29,277
Just a shotgun.

1113
01:18:30,289 --> 01:18:31,534
Just a shotgun.

1114
01:18:32,249 --> 01:18:34,289
Then let me have a look at that.

1115
01:18:47,807 --> 01:18:51,223
Little greaser son of a bitch is running
a goddamn bus service.

1116
01:18:51,310 --> 01:18:53,932
Thinks he can make a fool
out of Charlie Wade.

1117
01:18:54,313 --> 01:18:56,353
Get them wets out of the back.

1118
01:18:56,440 --> 01:18:57,899
See what we've got.

1119
01:19:02,446 --> 01:19:03,941
You killed him!

1120
01:19:04,657 --> 01:19:07,148
You got a talent
for stating the obvious, son.

1121
01:19:38,107 --> 01:19:39,518
Steve called for you.

1122
01:19:39,608 --> 01:19:40,604
Steve?

1123
01:19:40,901 --> 01:19:44,733
Steve.
Board of Education Steve, who likes you.

1124
01:19:45,489 --> 01:19:49,108
He goes for us hot-blooded Mexican girls,
I can tell.

1125
01:19:49,368 --> 01:19:52,038
Spanish. My mother would have
a heart attack.

1126
01:19:52,330 --> 01:19:54,287
Your mother's family is Spanish?

1127
01:19:54,373 --> 01:19:56,165
They go back to Cortés.

1128
01:19:56,250 --> 01:20:00,579
When he was riding by they were squatting
in a hut cooking hamsters for dinner.

1129
01:20:00,880 --> 01:20:04,498
You've got to be interested in somebody.
All you do is work.

1130
01:20:04,842 --> 01:20:07,878
All my mother does is work.
It's how you get to be Spanish.

1131
01:20:07,970 --> 01:20:09,678
How about this sheriff?

1132
01:20:10,097 --> 01:20:11,176
Sheriff?

1133
01:20:11,307 --> 01:20:13,596
The old high-school heartthrob sheriff?

1134
01:20:13,684 --> 01:20:15,891
I thought you were crazy about each other.

1135
01:20:15,978 --> 01:20:18,303
He's available. You're available.

1136
01:20:19,231 --> 01:20:21,722
I'm unmarried. I'm not available.

1137
01:20:21,901 --> 01:20:24,570
You told me one time it was true love.

1138
01:20:27,907 --> 01:20:30,445
Nobody stays in love for 23 years.

1139
01:21:07,989 --> 01:21:08,984
Let's go.

1140
01:21:10,950 --> 01:21:12,064
Goddamn it.

1141
01:21:13,536 --> 01:21:14,816
Come here. Come on.

1142
01:21:14,912 --> 01:21:18,495
- What the hell are you doing, asshole?
- How old is that girl?

1143
01:21:19,333 --> 01:21:21,456
Get your clothes in order, missy.

1144
01:21:21,544 --> 01:21:23,086
Where's your goddamn sense?

1145
01:21:23,170 --> 01:21:25,792
You got no fucking right!
Stay out of my life!

1146
01:21:26,841 --> 01:21:28,216
Give me the keys.

1147
01:21:28,300 --> 01:21:29,925
What should I do with her?

1148
01:21:30,011 --> 01:21:32,846
Drive her home.
Tell her mother where we found her.

1149
01:21:33,055 --> 01:21:35,463
- Leave her alone!
- Move it, boy!

1150
01:21:38,978 --> 01:21:41,303
Don't tell my mother. She'll kill me.

1151
01:21:41,397 --> 01:21:42,393
Pilar!

1152
01:21:42,732 --> 01:21:44,142
Don't eye me.

1153
01:21:44,233 --> 01:21:45,312
Git!

1154
01:24:41,160 --> 01:24:42,358
Follow me.

1155
01:25:08,813 --> 01:25:11,648
We thought we were something,
didn't we?

1156
01:25:14,819 --> 01:25:15,850
Yeah.

1157
01:25:19,031 --> 01:25:21,653
And I look at my kids in school...

1158
01:25:22,576 --> 01:25:24,735
...10th, 1 1th-graders.

1159
01:25:26,330 --> 01:25:28,572
That's who we were. Children.

1160
01:25:33,379 --> 01:25:35,751
I mean, what did we know about anything?

1161
01:25:40,511 --> 01:25:41,590
Nothing.

1162
01:25:45,391 --> 01:25:47,182
When Nando died...

1163
01:25:49,395 --> 01:25:51,055
...it was so sudden...

1164
01:25:53,316 --> 01:25:55,889
...I kind of went into shock for a while...

1165
01:25:57,486 --> 01:25:59,894
...and then I woke up and...

1166
01:26:00,740 --> 01:26:05,402
...there was the rest of my life
and I had no idea what to do with it.

1167
01:26:13,419 --> 01:26:15,910
You know, the other day you asked...

1168
01:26:17,381 --> 01:26:19,089
...why I came back.

1169
01:26:19,842 --> 01:26:20,838
Yeah?

1170
01:26:23,929 --> 01:26:26,088
I came back 'cause you were here.

1171
01:26:48,204 --> 01:26:51,454
My mother hasn't changed a song
since I was 10.

1172
01:29:14,183 --> 01:29:15,298
Wow.

1173
01:29:17,478 --> 01:29:18,806
Yeah.

1174
01:29:28,531 --> 01:29:30,689
How come it feels the same?

1175
01:29:33,077 --> 01:29:34,536
I don't know.

1176
01:29:35,538 --> 01:29:37,198
It just feels good.

1177
01:29:39,834 --> 01:29:41,162
Always did.

1178
01:29:49,176 --> 01:29:50,172
So....

1179
01:29:54,015 --> 01:29:56,553
What are we going to do about this?

1180
01:30:01,272 --> 01:30:02,303
More...

1181
01:30:03,482 --> 01:30:04,680
...I hope.

1182
01:30:34,263 --> 01:30:36,386
How long have you lived here?

1183
01:30:44,732 --> 01:30:45,930
Two years.

1184
01:30:46,901 --> 01:30:49,226
There's nothing on the walls.

1185
01:30:49,862 --> 01:30:51,237
No pictures.

1186
01:30:52,948 --> 01:30:54,359
I don't have kids.

1187
01:30:58,746 --> 01:31:00,324
Other pictures....

1188
01:31:02,083 --> 01:31:05,037
I don't know. It's nothing I want
to look back on.

1189
01:31:06,253 --> 01:31:08,127
Like your story's over.

1190
01:31:10,591 --> 01:31:12,418
I've felt that way...

1191
01:31:13,260 --> 01:31:14,090
...yeah.

1192
01:31:15,805 --> 01:31:16,919
It isn't.

1193
01:31:19,934 --> 01:31:21,096
Not by a long shot.

1194
01:31:25,773 --> 01:31:27,053
Pilar....

1195
01:31:31,737 --> 01:31:33,730
What was your father's name?

1196
01:31:34,740 --> 01:31:35,772
Eladio.

1197
01:31:36,784 --> 01:31:38,112
Eladio Cruz.

1198
01:32:28,669 --> 01:32:30,163
That's John Horse.

1199
01:32:31,297 --> 01:32:33,704
<i>The Spanish down in Florida call him...</i>

1200
01:32:33,883 --> 01:32:35,294
..."Juan Caballo."

1201
01:32:36,802 --> 01:32:38,047
John Horse.

1202
01:32:39,013 --> 01:32:40,721
He a black man or an Indian?

1203
01:32:40,806 --> 01:32:41,838
Both.

1204
01:32:42,808 --> 01:32:44,718
He was part of the Seminole nation.

1205
01:32:44,810 --> 01:32:48,475
<i>Got pushed down into the Florida</i>
<i>Everglades back in pioneer days.</i>

1206
01:32:49,273 --> 01:32:52,227
African people run off from slaveholders...

1207
01:32:52,610 --> 01:32:54,187
...hooked up with them...

1208
01:32:54,278 --> 01:32:56,437
...married up, had children.

1209
01:32:57,698 --> 01:33:00,450
When the Spanish gave up Florida...

1210
01:33:00,534 --> 01:33:04,117
<i>...the U.S. Army come down</i>
<i>to move all the Indian people to Oklahoma.</i>

1211
01:33:04,330 --> 01:33:05,824
<i>A couple of them held out.</i>

1212
01:33:06,207 --> 01:33:08,365
That man, John Horse...

1213
01:33:08,459 --> 01:33:10,950
...his friend, Wildcat, another fella named...

1214
01:33:11,045 --> 01:33:12,373
<i>...Osceola...</i>

1215
01:33:12,588 --> 01:33:14,248
<i>...formed a fighting band...</i>

1216
01:33:14,340 --> 01:33:17,294
...held out for another 10, 15 years...

1217
01:33:17,760 --> 01:33:21,674
...and beat zach Taylor and 1,000 troops
at Lake Okeechobee.

1218
01:33:23,599 --> 01:33:25,224
So they stayed in Florida?

1219
01:33:25,309 --> 01:33:28,346
One night they packed up,
rode out to Mexico.

1220
01:33:29,480 --> 01:33:32,683
Men went to work
for General Santa Anna down there.

1221
01:33:34,276 --> 01:33:38,654
After the Civil War they came north
to Texas, put up at Fort Duncan...

1222
01:33:38,990 --> 01:33:43,402
...and the men joined what was called
the Seminole Negro Indian Scouts.

1223
01:33:43,661 --> 01:33:44,823
The best trackers...

1224
01:33:44,912 --> 01:33:48,696
<i>...on either side of the border.</i>
<i>They chased after bandits...</i>

1225
01:33:49,333 --> 01:33:52,951
...rustlers, Texas rednecks,
Kiowas, Comanches....

1226
01:33:53,546 --> 01:33:55,752
They fought against the Indians?

1227
01:33:55,840 --> 01:33:57,417
Just like they did in Mexico.

1228
01:33:57,508 --> 01:33:59,299
But they were Indians themselves.

1229
01:34:00,219 --> 01:34:01,962
They were in the Army...

1230
01:34:02,221 --> 01:34:03,715
...like your father.

1231
01:34:06,809 --> 01:34:08,469
You know who I am?

1232
01:34:10,479 --> 01:34:12,389
I got a pretty good guess.

1233
01:34:13,357 --> 01:34:14,638
That guy who got shot.

1234
01:34:15,818 --> 01:34:18,523
You didn't go telling your father
you were here?

1235
01:34:18,696 --> 01:34:20,024
Are you kidding?

1236
01:34:20,531 --> 01:34:22,358
And face a court-martial?

1237
01:34:24,952 --> 01:34:26,197
Pretty tough old man.

1238
01:34:26,787 --> 01:34:28,614
Every time he moves up a rank...

1239
01:34:28,706 --> 01:34:31,707
<i>...he tightens the screws a little more.</i>
<i>Just 'cause....</i>

1240
01:34:32,918 --> 01:34:34,745
You know, he didn't have....

1241
01:34:36,881 --> 01:34:38,505
Didn't have a father.

1242
01:34:40,176 --> 01:34:42,168
He's still pissed off about it.

1243
01:34:44,388 --> 01:34:46,132
When you're his age...

1244
01:34:47,558 --> 01:34:50,227
...you'll still be pissed off about him.

1245
01:34:54,440 --> 01:34:56,231
How come you got into this?

1246
01:34:59,195 --> 01:35:00,938
These are our people.

1247
01:35:01,572 --> 01:35:05,440
There are Paynes in Florida,
Oklahoma, Piedras Negras--

1248
01:35:06,285 --> 01:35:07,566
So I'm part Indian?

1249
01:35:08,079 --> 01:35:09,739
By blood you are.

1250
01:35:11,207 --> 01:35:13,116
But blood only means what you let it.

1251
01:35:13,793 --> 01:35:17,790
My father says from the day you're born
you start from scratch.

1252
01:35:18,756 --> 01:35:19,621
No breaks.

1253
01:35:19,715 --> 01:35:20,830
<i>No excuses.</i>

1254
01:35:22,927 --> 01:35:25,169
You got to pull yourself up on your own.

1255
01:35:26,138 --> 01:35:28,464
He's living proof of that, son.

1256
01:35:30,643 --> 01:35:32,137
Living proof.

1257
01:35:40,319 --> 01:35:41,813
'Morning, Hollis.

1258
01:35:41,988 --> 01:35:43,019
Sam!

1259
01:35:43,114 --> 01:35:44,394
Sit down.

1260
01:35:45,700 --> 01:35:47,692
Big to-do the other day.

1261
01:35:49,036 --> 01:35:51,408
Meant a lot to folks you said something.

1262
01:35:52,248 --> 01:35:54,287
You thought anymore about our murder?

1263
01:35:56,168 --> 01:36:00,036
I wish I could tell you I remembered
something new, but I can't.

1264
01:36:03,426 --> 01:36:05,751
Well, I got an idea what happened.

1265
01:36:06,137 --> 01:36:07,168
You do?

1266
01:36:09,765 --> 01:36:13,893
I think somewhere between
Roderick Bledsoe's club and his house...

1267
01:36:13,978 --> 01:36:16,136
...Wade ran into Buddy Deeds.

1268
01:36:17,106 --> 01:36:19,264
I think Buddy put a bullet in him.

1269
01:36:19,608 --> 01:36:23,108
<i>Waited for him to die,</i>
<i>threw him in the trunk of the sheriff's car...</i>

1270
01:36:23,195 --> 01:36:25,651
<i>...and drove him out by Fort McKenzie.</i>

1271
01:36:27,158 --> 01:36:31,155
I think he buried him under four feet
of sand and never looked back.

1272
01:36:35,833 --> 01:36:38,122
You lived in the man's house, how long?

1273
01:36:39,128 --> 01:36:40,955
17, 18 years...

1274
01:36:42,298 --> 01:36:45,382
...but didn't get to know him
any better than that.

1275
01:36:46,385 --> 01:36:49,339
I got to go see somebody
up in San Antonio.

1276
01:36:51,599 --> 01:36:53,924
Now, your memory gets any better...

1277
01:36:54,143 --> 01:36:56,136
...I'll be back tonight.

1278
01:37:10,201 --> 01:37:11,909
She finally got up.

1279
01:37:13,287 --> 01:37:14,698
It's Saturday.

1280
01:37:15,206 --> 01:37:16,997
You got in late last night.

1281
01:37:17,416 --> 01:37:18,827
I had some...

1282
01:37:19,752 --> 01:37:21,626
...some school business.

1283
01:37:24,215 --> 01:37:25,460
Could I get this?

1284
01:37:27,218 --> 01:37:28,297
Paloma.

1285
01:37:28,678 --> 01:37:30,800
Nobody really wears that stuff.

1286
01:37:31,180 --> 01:37:34,347
Just 'cause you went to Catholic school
and wore a uniform.

1287
01:37:34,433 --> 01:37:36,759
I only went for my last two years.

1288
01:37:37,228 --> 01:37:38,556
How come?

1289
01:37:40,773 --> 01:37:43,394
My mother wanted
to keep me away from...

1290
01:37:46,153 --> 01:37:47,398
...from boys.

1291
01:37:48,322 --> 01:37:49,651
Did it work?

1292
01:37:53,494 --> 01:37:56,697
Longhorns go for 10 times the price.

1293
01:37:58,165 --> 01:38:00,917
But longhorns are hard
to come by these days.

1294
01:38:01,961 --> 01:38:03,420
Sell much out here?

1295
01:38:04,005 --> 01:38:06,959
How am I going to sell things?
Nobody comes around.

1296
01:38:07,299 --> 01:38:09,043
This stretch of road...

1297
01:38:09,135 --> 01:38:11,423
...runs between Nowhere and...

1298
01:38:12,096 --> 01:38:13,638
...Not Much Else.

1299
01:38:14,432 --> 01:38:16,590
A hell of a spot to put a business.

1300
01:38:17,310 --> 01:38:19,516
Don't see much competition, do you?

1301
01:38:20,730 --> 01:38:23,185
Used to sell these things like hotcakes.

1302
01:38:23,274 --> 01:38:24,436
Now...

1303
01:38:24,859 --> 01:38:28,192
...if it can't play those disks,
they won't look at it.

1304
01:38:29,530 --> 01:38:31,024
I like it here.

1305
01:38:31,991 --> 01:38:34,743
Once I tried going
onto the reservation to live.

1306
01:38:34,827 --> 01:38:36,618
Couldn't take the politics.

1307
01:38:36,704 --> 01:38:39,539
Damn Indians will drive you crazy
with that.

1308
01:38:42,585 --> 01:38:45,954
Now, your father,
this wasn't what he had in mind.

1309
01:38:47,298 --> 01:38:48,958
He come out of Korea...

1310
01:38:49,091 --> 01:38:51,926
...bought a Chevy with too much engine.

1311
01:38:52,386 --> 01:38:57,179
Used to come roaring up and down
this road all hours of the day and night...

1312
01:38:57,433 --> 01:38:59,509
...looking for somebody to race.

1313
01:39:05,024 --> 01:39:06,020
Here.

1314
01:39:07,360 --> 01:39:08,984
Buffalo chips.

1315
01:39:09,528 --> 01:39:11,320
<i>A fella down in Santa Fe told me...</i>

1316
01:39:11,405 --> 01:39:15,154
...he sells these as fast
as a buffalo can squeeze them out.

1317
01:39:21,123 --> 01:39:23,793
You think he killed anybody in Korea?

1318
01:39:25,044 --> 01:39:28,876
They don't hand those medals out
for hiding in your foxhole.

1319
01:39:31,759 --> 01:39:33,218
Would you buy this?

1320
01:39:35,554 --> 01:39:36,503
No.

1321
01:39:37,807 --> 01:39:39,716
Yeah, neither would I.

1322
01:39:41,560 --> 01:39:44,265
If he hadn't found the deputy's job...

1323
01:39:45,398 --> 01:39:49,941
...I believe Buddy might've gone down
the other path, got into serious trouble.

1324
01:39:50,444 --> 01:39:52,236
It settled him right down.

1325
01:39:52,321 --> 01:39:54,065
That and your mother.

1326
01:39:58,244 --> 01:40:00,616
Of course, he had that other one later.

1327
01:40:10,256 --> 01:40:11,833
He had another woman?

1328
01:40:13,718 --> 01:40:17,632
Your mother was not one
to be chased off her patch.

1329
01:40:18,306 --> 01:40:20,797
Half the damn county knew about it.

1330
01:40:21,642 --> 01:40:25,011
Nobody thought the worse of her
for seeing it through.

1331
01:40:25,104 --> 01:40:26,729
You know who it was?

1332
01:40:27,481 --> 01:40:28,810
The other one?

1333
01:40:29,567 --> 01:40:30,432
At my age...

1334
01:40:30,943 --> 01:40:32,354
<i>...you learn a new name...</i>

1335
01:40:32,445 --> 01:40:34,437
...you got to forget an old one.

1336
01:40:34,947 --> 01:40:35,943
Here.

1337
01:40:38,200 --> 01:40:41,901
This big fella was sleeping
in a crate at Cisco's junkyard.

1338
01:40:42,413 --> 01:40:45,580
When I was going to open
to see what was in her...

1339
01:40:45,875 --> 01:40:48,033
...jumped right at my face.

1340
01:40:49,086 --> 01:40:52,502
Scared me so bad I had to kill him
without thinking.

1341
01:40:53,007 --> 01:40:56,791
Be careful where you go poking.
Who knows what you'll find.

1342
01:41:35,800 --> 01:41:37,377
Private Johnson...

1343
01:41:40,096 --> 01:41:42,302
...are you unhappy...

1344
01:41:43,182 --> 01:41:44,297
...in the Army?

1345
01:41:44,517 --> 01:41:45,631
No, sir.

1346
01:41:47,144 --> 01:41:49,267
Then how would you explain...

1347
01:41:49,480 --> 01:41:51,686
...that out of 120 people...

1348
01:41:51,816 --> 01:41:53,725
...you were the only one...

1349
01:41:53,818 --> 01:41:56,106
<i>...who tested positive for drugs?</i>

1350
01:41:56,195 --> 01:41:57,737
I'm sorry, sir.

1351
01:42:00,074 --> 01:42:02,909
When you were given
the opportunity to enlist...

1352
01:42:03,369 --> 01:42:06,619
...a kind of contract was agreed upon.

1353
01:42:06,706 --> 01:42:09,541
I think the Army has honored its part...

1354
01:42:09,667 --> 01:42:10,912
...of that agreement.

1355
01:42:11,002 --> 01:42:11,997
Yes, sir.

1356
01:42:12,128 --> 01:42:14,797
Do you believe in what we do
in here, Private?

1357
01:42:15,423 --> 01:42:17,296
I can do the job, sir.

1358
01:42:24,348 --> 01:42:27,848
What exactly do you think your job is?

1359
01:42:30,062 --> 01:42:32,470
Follow orders, do whatever they say.

1360
01:42:32,690 --> 01:42:33,888
Who's "they"?

1361
01:42:35,026 --> 01:42:36,568
The officers.

1362
01:42:36,652 --> 01:42:38,194
And that's the job?

1363
01:42:39,030 --> 01:42:41,402
Nothing about serving your country?

1364
01:42:44,368 --> 01:42:47,120
These are not trick questions,
Private Johnson.

1365
01:42:47,538 --> 01:42:48,997
You'll get an Article 15...

1366
01:42:49,081 --> 01:42:52,284
<i>...and we'll go through the process</i>
<i>one way or another.</i>

1367
01:42:52,918 --> 01:42:55,326
I'm just trying to understand...

1368
01:42:56,714 --> 01:42:59,039
...how someone like you thinks.

1369
01:43:00,217 --> 01:43:02,009
You really want to know?

1370
01:43:02,178 --> 01:43:03,173
Please.

1371
01:43:05,681 --> 01:43:09,679
It's their country. This is one
of the best deals they offer.

1372
01:43:12,188 --> 01:43:14,513
How do you think I got to be a colonel?

1373
01:43:14,899 --> 01:43:17,472
Being good at your job.
Doing what they tell you.

1374
01:43:17,568 --> 01:43:18,979
Do what they tell you?

1375
01:43:19,070 --> 01:43:21,109
I mean, follow orders, sir.

1376
01:43:25,576 --> 01:43:27,901
With your attitude, Private...

1377
01:43:28,746 --> 01:43:31,202
...I'm surprised you want to stay
in the service.

1378
01:43:31,749 --> 01:43:32,947
I do, sir.

1379
01:43:33,709 --> 01:43:35,038
Because it's a job?

1380
01:43:37,380 --> 01:43:39,871
Outside it's such a mess. It's....

1381
01:43:44,637 --> 01:43:45,586
Chaos.

1382
01:43:48,933 --> 01:43:50,392
Why do you think...

1383
01:43:52,436 --> 01:43:54,762
...they let us in on the deal?

1384
01:43:58,401 --> 01:44:03,063
'Cause they got people to fight:
Arabs, yellow people, whatever.

1385
01:44:03,155 --> 01:44:04,947
Might as well use us.

1386
01:44:12,581 --> 01:44:14,574
It works like this, Private.

1387
01:44:15,418 --> 01:44:18,869
Every soldier in the war
doesn't have to believe...

1388
01:44:19,338 --> 01:44:21,247
...in what he's fighting for.

1389
01:44:22,049 --> 01:44:26,510
Most of them fight just to back up
the other soldiers in their squad.

1390
01:44:27,763 --> 01:44:29,756
You try not to get them killed.

1391
01:44:29,849 --> 01:44:32,256
You try not to get them extra duty.

1392
01:44:32,601 --> 01:44:35,057
You try not embarrass yourself...

1393
01:44:35,855 --> 01:44:37,349
...in front of them.

1394
01:44:51,412 --> 01:44:53,405
Why don't you start with that?

1395
01:44:54,415 --> 01:44:55,494
Yes, sir.

1396
01:44:59,837 --> 01:45:01,000
Dismissed.

1397
01:45:02,840 --> 01:45:04,299
Thank you, sir.

1398
01:45:33,871 --> 01:45:34,784
ANSELMA:

1399
01:45:40,586 --> 01:45:44,999
<i>Fred Zenito for Pager</i>
<i>and the Aggies jump to a 1 4-point lead.</i>

1400
01:45:45,132 --> 01:45:47,458
<i>Sooners back to punt on their own 27.</i>

1401
01:45:48,844 --> 01:45:53,471
Longhorns are going to kick some serious
butt this Saturday. You just watch.

1402
01:45:53,808 --> 01:45:57,888
We got a kid, a tailback from
down your way, out of El Indio--

1403
01:45:58,437 --> 01:45:59,979
That's in Maverick County.

1404
01:46:00,564 --> 01:46:02,059
Right, and you're in?

1405
01:46:02,149 --> 01:46:03,181
In Rio.

1406
01:46:03,442 --> 01:46:05,269
This kid, Hosea Brown...

1407
01:46:05,361 --> 01:46:06,855
...he does the 40 in 3.4.

1408
01:46:06,946 --> 01:46:09,698
Soft hands, lateral movement,
the whole package.

1409
01:46:09,782 --> 01:46:12,355
- Only a sophomore.
- Still go to all the home games?

1410
01:46:12,451 --> 01:46:16,449
Daddy's got his box in the stadium
and I'll fly to the Cowboy away games.

1411
01:46:16,914 --> 01:46:19,370
<i>And Friday nights there's high school.</i>

1412
01:46:19,458 --> 01:46:23,123
Churchill's got this boy, 6 foot 6,
310, moves like a cat.

1413
01:46:23,295 --> 01:46:26,830
High school, we're talking.
Guess how much he can bench-press?

1414
01:46:27,299 --> 01:46:28,628
Bunny, you....

1415
01:46:29,260 --> 01:46:31,051
You on that same medication?

1416
01:46:31,304 --> 01:46:33,130
- Why, do I seem jumpy?
- No.

1417
01:46:33,472 --> 01:46:35,714
You look good. I was just wondering.

1418
01:46:36,183 --> 01:46:39,884
Last year was awful with Mama
passing on and this business with O.J.

1419
01:46:39,979 --> 01:46:41,888
<i>It's not Don Meredith or...</i>

1420
01:46:41,981 --> 01:46:45,065
...one of our boys,
but it kind of threw me for a loop.

1421
01:46:45,318 --> 01:46:46,598
You look good.

1422
01:46:47,153 --> 01:46:49,774
Then that squeaker,
the Aggies dropped to Oklahoma.

1423
01:46:49,864 --> 01:46:53,992
That son of a bitch stepped in some
lucky shit before he kicked that goal.

1424
01:46:54,368 --> 01:46:58,152
If they hadn't pulled me off that woman,
I'd have jerked a knot in her.

1425
01:46:59,832 --> 01:47:01,374
Were you in a fight?

1426
01:47:02,376 --> 01:47:04,665
Daddy calls it an altercation.

1427
01:47:05,463 --> 01:47:07,751
How you doing, Sam? You look skinny.

1428
01:47:08,382 --> 01:47:11,004
No, I'm the same weight I always was.

1429
01:47:12,386 --> 01:47:15,506
Daddy hired a pinhead to take your job.
Says so himself:

1430
01:47:15,723 --> 01:47:18,926
<i>"Even my son-in-law was better</i>
<i>than this pinhead I got now."</i>

1431
01:47:19,018 --> 01:47:20,133
Bunny....

1432
01:47:22,480 --> 01:47:25,053
That stuff I left in the garage still there?

1433
01:47:26,567 --> 01:47:30,268
Least he never called me that.
With me it was always "high-strung."

1434
01:47:30,363 --> 01:47:33,981
"Bunny would've done something
with her life if she wasn't so high-strung."

1435
01:47:34,075 --> 01:47:35,699
Or "tightly wound."

1436
01:47:36,327 --> 01:47:38,865
You haven't had one of your fires,
have you?

1437
01:47:40,039 --> 01:47:43,906
The stuff I left in the garage,
some of it was my father's.

1438
01:47:44,710 --> 01:47:46,667
Did you watch the draft this year?

1439
01:47:48,255 --> 01:47:51,541
Of course not. Idiot question.
They try to make it dramatic...

1440
01:47:51,634 --> 01:47:54,551
...like it's a surprise who picks who
in the first round...

1441
01:47:54,637 --> 01:47:58,966
...but they went over it for months
with their experts, computers...

1442
01:47:59,183 --> 01:48:02,184
...doctor's reports, coach's evaluations...

1443
01:48:02,353 --> 01:48:05,769
...highlight reels, psychological profiles....

1444
01:48:06,524 --> 01:48:11,351
I wouldn't be surprised if they collected
stool samples on them, had them analyzed.

1445
01:48:11,529 --> 01:48:12,940
All that to pick...

1446
01:48:13,030 --> 01:48:15,237
...a football player for your squad.

1447
01:48:16,158 --> 01:48:20,452
Compared to that, what you know about
a person when you get married to them...

1448
01:48:20,538 --> 01:48:22,993
...doesn't amount to diddly, does it?

1449
01:48:25,835 --> 01:48:27,543
No, I suppose not.

1450
01:48:28,045 --> 01:48:31,663
You kind of bought yourself
a pig in a poke, didn't you?

1451
01:48:32,717 --> 01:48:37,628
The whole time we were seeing each other,
you didn't know that I was tightly wound.

1452
01:48:38,014 --> 01:48:40,006
It wasn't just you, Bunny.

1453
01:48:41,058 --> 01:48:42,885
No, it wasn't, was it?

1454
01:48:44,270 --> 01:48:47,853
You didn't exactly throw yourself
into it heart and soul.

1455
01:48:50,901 --> 01:48:54,484
Your shit's still in the garage,
if that's what you came for.

1456
01:49:06,751 --> 01:49:08,743
Three hundred and fifty pounds.

1457
01:49:12,715 --> 01:49:16,582
That boy Churchill's got.
He plays tackle both ways.

1458
01:49:19,096 --> 01:49:21,338
Bench-presses 350 pounds.

1459
01:49:24,226 --> 01:49:27,144
Imagine having that much weight on you,
pressing down.

1460
01:49:27,229 --> 01:49:29,899
Be hard to breathe, hard to swallow.

1461
01:49:31,275 --> 01:49:35,189
I think they have another fella there
to keep it off your chest.

1462
01:49:37,239 --> 01:49:38,402
A spotter.

1463
01:49:39,492 --> 01:49:42,991
"I only got my little girl now," he says.

1464
01:49:43,204 --> 01:49:44,912
"She's my lifeline."

1465
01:49:46,791 --> 01:49:50,740
Then he says I can't sit in the box anymore
if I don't control myself.

1466
01:49:51,253 --> 01:49:52,285
Son of a bitch!

1467
01:49:52,380 --> 01:49:55,464
<i>He doesn't even watch the games,</i>
<i>just sits there drinking.</i>

1468
01:49:55,549 --> 01:49:57,209
Looks up at the TV now and then.

1469
01:49:57,301 --> 01:50:01,002
I'd be better off in the cheap seats
with some real football people.

1470
01:50:01,889 --> 01:50:03,549
You look good, Bunny.

1471
01:50:04,976 --> 01:50:06,767
It was nice to see you.

1472
01:50:09,438 --> 01:50:10,434
Thanks.

1473
01:50:12,316 --> 01:50:14,807
I like it when you say that, Sam.

1474
01:50:40,177 --> 01:50:41,755
"Dearest Buddy."

1475
01:50:52,773 --> 01:50:54,481
Hey, it's the general.

1476
01:50:56,193 --> 01:50:58,482
Colonel. Is Otis in?

1477
01:50:58,654 --> 01:51:00,314
- Come on in.
- If it's too late--

1478
01:51:00,406 --> 01:51:01,651
Come on in.

1479
01:51:10,291 --> 01:51:14,620
Otis is sitting up with some people
at the club. I don't think he'll be long.

1480
01:51:22,762 --> 01:51:25,846
His hot sauce recipe
won a contest last year.

1481
01:51:26,265 --> 01:51:28,009
They're selling it as far away...

1482
01:51:28,100 --> 01:51:29,476
...as San Antonio.

1483
01:51:30,478 --> 01:51:33,016
You've been in this house for a while?

1484
01:51:33,773 --> 01:51:38,150
I've been here with him eight years.
He built it when he was with Leora.

1485
01:51:39,111 --> 01:51:40,487
Never met her.

1486
01:51:41,322 --> 01:51:43,647
There's a bunch of them you never met.

1487
01:51:43,824 --> 01:51:45,484
Well, me neither.

1488
01:51:47,328 --> 01:51:49,653
Let me show you around.

1489
01:52:04,804 --> 01:52:08,173
He got into this cowboys-and-Indians stuff
a while back.

1490
01:52:08,474 --> 01:52:10,016
Spent half his time poking...

1491
01:52:10,101 --> 01:52:12,508
...around the library, way up to Austin.

1492
01:52:33,332 --> 01:52:35,372
Kind of like a shrine, isn't it?

1493
01:52:37,545 --> 01:52:39,584
Where did he get all this stuff?

1494
01:52:39,755 --> 01:52:41,712
Your mother's got a brother, Alphonse.

1495
01:52:42,591 --> 01:52:43,457
Uncle Al.

1496
01:52:43,551 --> 01:52:47,383
Otis stood on good terms
with him. Whenever you make the news...

1497
01:52:47,513 --> 01:52:48,888
...he sends it on.

1498
01:52:49,557 --> 01:52:51,514
When they made you general...

1499
01:52:51,726 --> 01:52:54,513
...Otis almost drove away
our customers going on about it.

1500
01:52:54,603 --> 01:52:55,932
I'm a colonel.

1501
01:52:56,522 --> 01:52:57,518
I know.

1502
01:52:58,190 --> 01:53:01,061
The man made me memorize
the whole Army chain of command...

1503
01:53:01,152 --> 01:53:02,860
...before he'd marry me.

1504
01:53:06,991 --> 01:53:09,743
My mother said that
he never asked about me.

1505
01:53:11,162 --> 01:53:12,822
He never asked her.

1506
01:53:23,466 --> 01:53:25,043
Tell him I stopped by?

1507
01:53:25,676 --> 01:53:26,755
Thanks.

1508
01:53:31,265 --> 01:53:32,546
Catch you later...

1509
01:53:34,393 --> 01:53:35,556
...Colonel.

1510
01:53:43,611 --> 01:53:44,560
JAIME:

1511
01:53:53,245 --> 01:53:54,159
ENRIQUE:

1512
01:54:01,629 --> 01:54:02,542
ANSELMA:

1513
01:54:08,344 --> 01:54:10,420
<i>Señora Cruz.</i>

1514
01:54:12,264 --> 01:54:13,379
Who is it?

1515
01:54:17,311 --> 01:54:20,312
What are you doing out here?
Are you crazy?

1516
01:54:24,694 --> 01:54:27,363
In English. We're in the United States.

1517
01:54:27,613 --> 01:54:31,362
I have some friends
and they have had an accident.

1518
01:54:32,660 --> 01:54:35,151
- You have somebody else out there?
- We was...

1519
01:54:35,246 --> 01:54:38,994
...by the river and I heard my friend
calling for help...

1520
01:54:39,542 --> 01:54:40,917
<i>...and I look...</i>

1521
01:54:41,460 --> 01:54:43,370
...and she has fallen in the water.

1522
01:54:43,462 --> 01:54:45,455
Don't tell me lies. What happened?

1523
01:54:47,133 --> 01:54:49,291
We was crossing the river.

1524
01:54:54,890 --> 01:54:56,800
What are you doing out there?

1525
01:54:56,934 --> 01:54:59,306
Wait. Who are they?
Why bring them here?

1526
01:54:59,562 --> 01:55:01,104
I need help, <i>señora</i>.

1527
01:55:06,736 --> 01:55:09,772
I'll call Border Patrol.
They'll get her to the hospital.

1528
01:55:09,864 --> 01:55:10,860
ENRIQUE:

1529
01:55:11,365 --> 01:55:13,773
You think you're doing
these people a favor?

1530
01:55:13,868 --> 01:55:16,619
What are they going to do?
They get on welfare...

1531
01:55:16,704 --> 01:55:18,531
...or they become criminals.

1532
01:55:44,690 --> 01:55:46,647
This girl is a friend of yours?

1533
01:55:48,653 --> 01:55:50,147
I thought you were married.

1534
01:55:50,363 --> 01:55:54,574
I am married to the cousin of a friend
but only to live here.

1535
01:55:55,034 --> 01:55:56,825
This is the mother of my child.

1536
01:55:58,663 --> 01:55:59,694
Typical.

1537
01:56:10,132 --> 01:56:11,212
Homework?

1538
01:56:13,010 --> 01:56:14,552
I finished that.

1539
01:56:14,845 --> 01:56:16,505
I'm just messing around.

1540
01:56:20,685 --> 01:56:21,799
Tanks, huh?

1541
01:56:22,478 --> 01:56:23,806
Yeah, well....

1542
01:56:24,271 --> 01:56:27,937
If you've got to be in the Army,
better to have something slick to drive.

1543
01:56:28,025 --> 01:56:29,021
So....

1544
01:56:30,277 --> 01:56:32,021
You're going in the Army?

1545
01:56:34,782 --> 01:56:36,905
That's the general plan, isn't it?

1546
01:56:42,331 --> 01:56:43,825
That's up to you.

1547
01:56:47,920 --> 01:56:50,079
The Army isn't for everybody.

1548
01:56:57,346 --> 01:57:00,181
It's not that I think
you wouldn't be good at it.

1549
01:57:00,683 --> 01:57:01,846
<i>You know....</i>

1550
01:57:04,145 --> 01:57:08,557
I wouldn't be disappointed if you decided
to do something else with your life.

1551
01:57:11,319 --> 01:57:12,350
You wouldn't?

1552
01:57:14,822 --> 01:57:15,771
No.

1553
01:57:24,123 --> 01:57:25,238
So....

1554
01:57:27,001 --> 01:57:28,993
How's your room shaping up?

1555
01:57:30,629 --> 01:57:32,788
It's fine. I'm pretty much moved in.

1556
01:57:32,882 --> 01:57:34,044
Good.

1557
01:57:39,388 --> 01:57:41,345
Are we ever going to see your father?

1558
01:57:41,891 --> 01:57:43,053
My father?

1559
01:57:43,392 --> 01:57:44,637
He lives here, right?

1560
01:57:44,727 --> 01:57:45,890
Yes, he does.

1561
01:57:52,735 --> 01:57:54,229
Maybe we'll....

1562
01:57:54,904 --> 01:57:57,821
We'll fix that thing out back and have...

1563
01:57:58,240 --> 01:57:59,272
...a barbecue.

1564
01:57:59,992 --> 01:58:01,652
<i>We could invite him and...</i>

1565
01:58:01,744 --> 01:58:03,404
...and his wife over.

1566
01:58:06,624 --> 01:58:08,451
He makes his own sauce.

1567
01:58:19,845 --> 01:58:20,675
ELADIO:

1568
01:59:07,059 --> 01:59:09,182
<i>Let's go! Hurry up!</i>

1569
01:59:09,895 --> 01:59:12,351
Everybody in the world will see.

1570
01:59:15,151 --> 01:59:16,978
He was a doctor on the other side.

1571
01:59:18,904 --> 01:59:20,315
Don't worry about it.

1572
01:59:21,782 --> 01:59:23,609
He owes me a few favors.

1573
01:59:29,457 --> 01:59:32,244
In English, Enrique. In English!

1574
01:59:38,799 --> 01:59:39,831
Hollis!

1575
01:59:44,013 --> 01:59:45,009
Hollis!

1576
01:59:47,350 --> 01:59:48,808
You in there?

1577
02:00:13,626 --> 02:00:14,622
Fellas.

1578
02:00:22,635 --> 02:00:24,129
You're open late.

1579
02:00:24,887 --> 02:00:27,639
I'm not open. We're just talking.

1580
02:00:35,314 --> 02:00:37,307
So, Hollis probably told you.

1581
02:00:37,942 --> 02:00:39,816
We found Charlie Wade.

1582
02:00:40,778 --> 02:00:42,272
Is that right?

1583
02:00:43,406 --> 02:00:46,857
Start digging holes in this county,
no telling what'll come up.

1584
02:00:48,828 --> 02:00:50,737
You two saw it, didn't you?

1585
02:00:53,666 --> 02:00:56,157
You two saw it when Buddy killed him.

1586
02:01:00,172 --> 02:01:02,663
I'm going to find out one way or the other.

1587
02:01:03,300 --> 02:01:06,337
Your father had the finest sense
of justice...

1588
02:01:06,512 --> 02:01:08,469
...of any man I've ever known.

1589
02:01:08,973 --> 02:01:10,965
And my mother was a saint.

1590
02:01:13,185 --> 02:01:15,937
For 15 years the whole damn town...

1591
02:01:16,272 --> 02:01:18,941
...knew he had another woman on the side.

1592
02:01:22,528 --> 02:01:25,233
He stole $10,000
and set her up in business...

1593
02:01:25,364 --> 02:01:27,108
...but hell, what's that?

1594
02:01:27,867 --> 02:01:30,192
You got a problem, old Buddy'll fix it.

1595
02:01:30,703 --> 02:01:32,909
You facing some time in jail?

1596
02:01:33,122 --> 02:01:37,202
Buddy'll knock half of it off,
if you do what he says when he says.

1597
02:01:38,461 --> 02:01:41,082
You got some business
that's not exactly legal?

1598
02:01:41,172 --> 02:01:42,370
Just talk to Buddy.

1599
02:01:42,465 --> 02:01:43,496
Buddy Deeds--

1600
02:01:43,591 --> 02:01:45,418
Buddy Deeds was a murderer.

1601
02:01:47,386 --> 02:01:48,845
That night at the cafe...

1602
02:01:49,221 --> 02:01:52,388
...he didn't stay long after you left,
did he, Hollis?

1603
02:01:53,643 --> 02:01:56,679
Maybe he'd decided
he'd gone too far with Wade.

1604
02:01:56,771 --> 02:02:00,187
He figured he'd better not wait
for the sheriff to get behind him.

1605
02:02:00,274 --> 02:02:02,896
So he stepped out to see
if he could catch up...

1606
02:02:06,364 --> 02:02:08,855
...and you were here that night...

1607
02:02:09,450 --> 02:02:11,158
...weren't you, "O"?

1608
02:02:13,079 --> 02:02:14,359
I was here.

1609
02:02:17,875 --> 02:02:21,209
I'd been running a game
on the side after hours.

1610
02:02:23,047 --> 02:02:24,292
Craps.

1611
02:02:25,007 --> 02:02:27,249
Draw poker on the weekends.

1612
02:02:28,803 --> 02:02:30,961
Roderick didn't know about it.

1613
02:02:31,847 --> 02:02:33,342
More important...

1614
02:02:33,933 --> 02:02:36,602
...Charlie Wade didn't know about it...

1615
02:02:36,978 --> 02:02:39,978
...'cause I didn't want to cut him in on it.

1616
02:02:41,732 --> 02:02:44,899
I was pretty full of myself
back in those days.

1617
02:02:46,112 --> 02:02:49,896
Hell, I just didn't expect the man so early.

1618
02:05:01,163 --> 02:05:02,112
Wade!

1619
02:05:48,085 --> 02:05:51,786
Sheriff Charlie was the whip hand
for old Judge Tibbs...

1620
02:05:52,173 --> 02:05:55,043
<i>...who pretty much owned</i>
<i>this county back then.</i>

1621
02:05:56,093 --> 02:05:58,002
<i>If the truth came out...</i>

1622
02:05:58,638 --> 02:06:01,307
<i>...he wasn't going to go easy on Hollis.</i>

1623
02:06:03,851 --> 02:06:06,603
I don't know why I trusted Buddy with it...

1624
02:06:08,022 --> 02:06:10,145
...don't know why he trusted me.

1625
02:06:13,527 --> 02:06:15,354
The first time I talked with him...

1626
02:06:15,446 --> 02:06:17,486
...was right there and then...

1627
02:06:18,491 --> 02:06:22,488
...with a dead white man leaking blood
on the floor between us.

1628
02:06:23,037 --> 02:06:26,987
The three of us cleaned up
and took him out by the post...

1629
02:06:27,708 --> 02:06:29,250
...and put him under.

1630
02:06:30,503 --> 02:06:32,495
I can't say I was much help.

1631
02:06:33,047 --> 02:06:34,874
And the $10,000?

1632
02:06:35,800 --> 02:06:37,377
Widow's benefits.

1633
02:06:38,094 --> 02:06:40,929
He figured it'd make
the disappearance look better.

1634
02:06:41,055 --> 02:06:44,839
And Mercedes was scraping by
after Charlie killed her man.

1635
02:06:46,352 --> 02:06:47,597
Buddy and her...

1636
02:06:47,687 --> 02:06:49,893
<i>...didn't get hooked up until later.</i>

1637
02:06:50,773 --> 02:06:52,600
Time went on...

1638
02:06:52,692 --> 02:06:54,768
...people liked the story we told...

1639
02:06:54,860 --> 02:06:57,482
...better than what the truth
might have been.

1640
02:06:58,698 --> 02:07:00,358
It's your call, Sam.

1641
02:07:02,368 --> 02:07:05,369
I don't think the Rangers are likely to...

1642
02:07:05,830 --> 02:07:08,665
...find out any more
than they already know.

1643
02:07:11,752 --> 02:07:13,412
And as for me...

1644
02:07:16,882 --> 02:07:19,718
...it's just one of your unsolved mysteries.

1645
02:07:28,978 --> 02:07:31,433
Word gets out who the body was...

1646
02:07:32,523 --> 02:07:34,646
...people'll think Buddy done it.

1647
02:07:37,945 --> 02:07:39,938
Buddy's a goddamn legend.

1648
02:07:41,782 --> 02:07:43,407
He can handle it.

1649
02:07:49,582 --> 02:07:51,076
'Night, fellas.

1650
02:08:19,028 --> 02:08:21,021
When does the picture start?

1651
02:08:24,200 --> 02:08:27,699
Are you going to tell your mother
we've been seeing each other?

1652
02:08:28,120 --> 02:08:30,327
She'll find out sooner or later.

1653
02:08:30,498 --> 02:08:34,116
I don't have to ask permission anymore,
if that's what you mean.

1654
02:08:40,174 --> 02:08:42,712
You have any idea when your father died?

1655
02:08:42,802 --> 02:08:43,797
Eladio?

1656
02:08:45,137 --> 02:08:47,426
Couple of months before I was born.

1657
02:08:50,017 --> 02:08:52,093
Try a year and half.

1658
02:09:11,831 --> 02:09:15,875
Buddy bought the cafe for her
with money he took from the county.

1659
02:09:19,630 --> 02:09:21,670
They can't pull this on me.

1660
02:09:22,800 --> 02:09:24,211
It's not fair.

1661
02:09:29,557 --> 02:09:31,134
I don't believe this.

1662
02:09:38,524 --> 02:09:41,442
He paid the hospital bill
when you were born.

1663
02:09:44,822 --> 02:09:46,102
Your mother...

1664
02:09:47,074 --> 02:09:48,983
...she always called you...

1665
02:09:49,452 --> 02:09:51,278
..."a beautiful daughter"...

1666
02:09:52,413 --> 02:09:54,619
...in the letters she wrote to him.

1667
02:10:01,839 --> 02:10:04,591
From the first time I saw you at school...

1668
02:10:14,393 --> 02:10:18,094
...all those years we were married
to other people, I always felt...

1669
02:10:19,190 --> 02:10:21,099
...like we were connected.

1670
02:10:26,030 --> 02:10:27,773
I remember thinking...

1671
02:10:29,450 --> 02:10:31,822
...you were the one part of my life...

1672
02:10:32,703 --> 02:10:34,910
...that Buddy didn't have a piece of.

1673
02:10:36,082 --> 02:10:38,370
I can't have any more children.

1674
02:10:39,043 --> 02:10:41,285
After Amado, I had complications.

1675
02:10:41,379 --> 02:10:44,961
I can't get pregnant anymore,
if that's what the rule is about.

1676
02:10:49,053 --> 02:10:50,381
So that's it?

1677
02:10:52,723 --> 02:10:55,214
You won't want to be with me anymore?

1678
02:10:58,854 --> 02:11:00,313
If I met you...

1679
02:11:02,066 --> 02:11:04,189
...for the first time today...

1680
02:11:05,486 --> 02:11:07,562
...I'd still want to be with you.

1681
02:11:13,202 --> 02:11:15,029
Start from scratch?

1682
02:11:16,497 --> 02:11:17,446
Yeah.

1683
02:11:19,166 --> 02:11:22,037
All that other stuff and all that history...

1684
02:11:22,962 --> 02:11:24,753
...the hell with it, right?

1685
02:11:30,761 --> 02:11:32,339
Forget the Alamo.

